PATO:0001241.definition: A quality which inheres in a continuant.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: quality of a single physical entity
multiply inhering quality of a physical entity
quality of a single physical entity
multiply inhering quality of a physical entity

IAO:0000015.label: information carrier
IAO:0000015.definition: A quality of an information bearer that imparts the information content

PATO:0001237.label: quality of a single physical entity
PATO:0001237.definition: A physical object quality which inheres in a single-bearer.

PATO:0000001.label: quality
PATO:0000001.definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

BFO:0000017.label: realizable entity
BFO:0000017.definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

OBI:0000202.label: investigation agent role
OBI:0000202.definition: A role borne by an entity and that is realized in a process that is part of an investigation in which an objective is achieved. These processes include, among others: planning, overseeing, funding, reviewing.

OBI:0000571.label: manufacturer role
OBI:0000571.definition: Manufacturer role is a role which inheres in a person or organization and which is realized by a manufacturing process.

CHEBI:50906.label: role
CHEBI:50906.definition: A role is particular behaviour which a material entity may exhibit.

OBI:0000947.label: service provider role
OBI:0000947.definition: is a role which inheres in a person or organization and is realized in in a planned process which provides access to training, materials or execution of protocols for an organization or person

AGRO:00000069.label: biological pest control agent role
AGRO:00000069.definition: A role that inheres in an organism that is realised in a pest control process where that organism is used to suppress unwanted organisms.

AGRO:00002001.label: crop role
AGRO:00002001.definition: A role that inheres in an organism that is harvested for food, clothing, livestock,fodder, biofuel, medicine, or other uses.

AGRO:00002004.label: draft animal role
AGRO:00002004.definition: A role that inheres in an animal that is kept by humans and trained to perform tasks.

OBI:0000067.label: evaluant role
OBI:0000067.definition: a role that inheres in a material entity that is realized in an assay in which data is generated about the bearer of the evaluant role

AGRO:00002005.label: human power role
AGRO:00002005.definition: A role that inheres in a human to power an implement.

AGRO:00000008.label: irrigation water source role
AGRO:00000008.definition: A role that inheres in a water body that is realised in an irrigation process where water is transported from that water body to the target of the irrigation process.

AGRO:00000070.label: liming role
AGRO:00000070.definition: A role that inheres in an environmental material that is realised in a land preparation process where that environmental material is applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

OBI:0000319.label: material to be added role
OBI:0000319.definition: material to be added role is a protocol participant role realized by a material which is added into a material bearing the target of material addition role in a material addition process

AGRO:00000033.label: organic fertilizer role
AGRO:00000033.definition: A fertilizer that is derived from animal or vegetable matter, and contains a carbon-hydrogen linkage.

AGRO:00000378.label: person role within the experiment
AGRO:00000378.definition: Roled performed by a person during an experiment.

AGRO:00000035.label: pest role
AGRO:00000035.definition: A role that inheres in an organism that is realized in an agricultural process where the organism is unwanted.

OBI:0000017.label: regulatory role
OBI:0000017.definition: a role which inheres in material entities and is realized in the processes of making, enforcing or being defined by legislation or orders issued by a governmental body.

OBI:0000112.label: specimen role
OBI:0000112.definition: a role borne by a material entity that is gained during a specimen collection process and that can be realized by use of the specimen in an investigation

OBI:0000444.label: target of material addition role
OBI:0000444.definition: target of material addition role is a role realized by an entity into which a material is added in a material addition process

ENVO:01000665.label: waste role
ENVO:01000665.definition: A role that is realized in some process wherein the bearer is discarded or not utilized further.

ENVO:00010483.label: environmental material
ENVO:00010483.definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.

ENVO:01000813.label: astronomical body part
ENVO:01000813.definition: A material part of an astronomical body.

PCO:0000000.label: collection of organisms
PCO:0000000.definition: A material entity that consists of two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids.

ENVO:01000408.label: environmental zone
ENVO:01000408.definition: A site which has its extent determined by the presence or influence of one or more components of an environmental system or the processes occurring therein.

ENVO:00002004.label: physical object of mesoscopic geological size
ENVO:00002004.definition: An environmental feature that is, or can be, contained and is predominantly composed of one or a few types of stuff.

ENVO:01000804.label: astronomical object
ENVO:01000804.definition: An object which is composed of one or more gravitationally bound structures that are associated with a position in space.

ENVO:01001008.label: meteor
ENVO:01001008.definition: A meteor is any matter- or energy-based entity which is located in the atmosphere of an astronomical body.

AGRO:00000357.label: weather station
AGRO:00000357.definition: An observation post where weather conditions and meteorological data are observed and recorded and reported.

IAO:0000030.label: information content entity
IAO:0000030.definition: A generically dependent continuant that is about some thing.

CHEBI:24431.label: chemical entity
CHEBI:24431.definition: A chemical entity is a physical entity of interest in chemistry including molecular entities, parts thereof, and chemical substances.

ENVO:00002297.label: environmental feature
ENVO:00002297.definition: A material entity which determines an environmental system.

OBI:0000835.label: manufacturer
OBI:0000835.definition: A person or organization that has a manufacturer role

OBI:1110108.label: material to be added
OBI:1110108.definition: a material that is added to another one in a material combination process

PO:0025131.label: plant anatomical entity
PO:0025131.definition: An anatomical entity that is or was part of a plant.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 植物 解剖学（形態）的実体 (Japanese, exact)

CHEBI:36342.label: subatomic particle
CHEBI:36342.definition: A particle smaller than an atom.

RO:0002577.label: system
RO:0002577.definition: A material entity consisting of multiple components that are causally integrated.

OBI:1110109.label: target of material addition
OBI:1110109.definition: A material entity into which another is being added in a material combinatino process

OBI:0002076.label: collection of specimens
OBI:0002076.definition: A material entity that has two or more specimens as its parts.

FOODON:03400361.label: food product type
FOODON:03400361.definition: A food product type is a class of food products that is differentiated by its food composition, processing and/or consumption characteristics. This does not include brand name products but it may include generic food dish categories.

IAO:0000178.label: material information bearer
IAO:0000178.definition: A material entity in which a concretization of an information content entity inheres.

OBI:0100026.label: organism
OBI:0100026.definition: A material entity that is an individual living system, such as animal, plant, bacteria or virus, that is capable of replicating or reproducing, growth and maintenance in the right environment. An organism may be unicellular or made up, like humans, of many billions of cells divided into specialized tissues and organs.

PCO:0000031.label: organismal entity
PCO:0000031.definition: A material entity that is one or more organisms, viruses or viroids.

OBI:0000245.label: organization
OBI:0000245.definition: An entity that can bear roles, has members, and has a set of organization rules. Members of organizations are either organizations themselves or individual people. Members can bear specific organization member roles that are determined in the organization rules. The organization rules also determine how decisions are made on behalf of the organization by the organization members.

FOODON:03420116.label: part of plant or animal
FOODON:03420116.definition: Anatomical part of the plant or animal from which the food product or its major ingredient is derived, e.g., *LEAF*, *ROOT OR TUBER*, *ORGAN MEAT*, *MILK* OR *EGG*; it also includes components of parts, such as *CREAM*, and extracts, concentrates or isolates, such as *PROTEIN EXTRACT* or *SUGAR*.

OBI:0000181.label: population
OBI:0000181.definition: a population is a collection of individuals from the same taxonomic class living, counted or sampled at a particular site or in a particular area

OBI:0000047.label: processed material
OBI:0000047.definition: Is a material entity that is created or changed during material processing.

OBI:0100051.label: specimen
OBI:0100051.definition: A material entity that has the specimen role.

PO:0009049.label: inflorescence
PO:0009049.definition: A reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that has as parts all of the shoot axes (PO:0025029) and flowers (PO:0009046; must have two or more) distal to the most distal leaf (PO:0009025).

FOODON:03420167.label: fruit part
FOODON:03420167.definition: The fleshy fruit of any plant. *FRUIT* includes vegetables berries and pods as well. The bulk of a fruit is its fleshy part, which is covered by a peel (skin) and which encloses a core, pit or seeds.

CHEBI:16134.label: ammonia
CHEBI:16134.definition: An azane that consists of a single nitrogen atom covelently bonded to three hydrogen atoms.

CHEBI:16526.label: carbon dioxide
CHEBI:16526.definition: A one-carbon compound with formula CO2 in which the carbon is attached to each oxygen atom by a double bond. A colourless, odourless gas under normal conditions, it is produced during respiration by all animals, fungi and microorganisms that depend directly or indirectly on living or decaying plants for food.

CHEBI:17997.label: dinitrogen
CHEBI:17997.definition: An elemental molecule consisting of two trivalently-bonded nitrogen atoms.

CHEBI:17883.label: hydrogen chloride
CHEBI:17883.definition: A mononuclear parent hydride consisting of covalently bonded hydrogen and chlorine atoms.

CHEBI:16136.label: hydrogen sulfide
CHEBI:16136.definition: A sulfur hydride consisting of a single sulfur atom bonded to two hydrogen atoms. A highly poisonous, flammable gas with a characteristic odour of rotten eggs, it is often produced by bacterial decomposition of organic matter in the absence of oxygen.

CHEBI:32285.label: ((13)C)urea
CHEBI:32285.definition: A (13)C-modified compound that is urea in which the carbon is present as its (13)C isotope.

CHEBI:139357.label: (13)C-modified compound
CHEBI:139357.definition: An isotopically modified compound in which the abundance of a (13)C isotope at one or more positions has been increased above that of the naturally occurring level.

CHEBI:39142.label: Bronsted base
CHEBI:39142.definition: A molecular entity capable of accepting a hydron from a donor (Bronsted acid).

CHEBI:17996.label: chloride
CHEBI:17996.definition: A halide anion formed when chlorine picks up an electron to form an an anion.

CHEBI:39141.label: Bronsted acid
CHEBI:39141.definition: A molecular entity capable of donating a hydron to an acceptor (Bronsted base).

CHEBI:39144.label: Lewis base
CHEBI:39144.definition: A molecular entity able to provide a pair of electrons and thus capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron-pair acceptor (Lewis acid), thereby producing a Lewis adduct.

CHEBI:16698.label: cyanamide
CHEBI:16698.definition: A nitrile that is hydrogen cyanide in which the hydrogen has been replaced by an amino group.

CHEBI:37838.label: carboacyl group
CHEBI:37838.definition: A carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of at least one OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

CHEBI:25696.label: organic anion
CHEBI:25696.definition: Any organic ion with a net negative charge.

CHEBI:33273.label: polyatomic anion
CHEBI:33273.definition: An anion consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:33259.label: elemental molecular entity
CHEBI:33259.definition: A molecular entity all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

CHEBI:24835.label: inorganic molecular entity
CHEBI:24835.definition: A molecular entity that contains no carbon.

CHEBI:24870.label: ion
CHEBI:24870.definition: A molecular entity having a net electric charge.

CHEBI:139358.label: isotopically modified compound
CHEBI:139358.definition: Any molecular entity in which the isotopic ratio of nuclides for at least one element deviates measurably from that occurring in nature. The term includes both isotopically substituted compounds (in which essentially all the molecules of the compound have only the indicated nuclide(s) at each designated position) and isotopically labeled compounds (a formal mixture of an isotopically unmodified compound with one or more analogous isotopically substituted compound(s).

CHEBI:33579.label: main group molecular entity
CHEBI:33579.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms from any of groups 1, 2, 13, 14, 15, 16, 17, and 18 of the periodic table.

CHEBI:36357.label: polyatomic entity
CHEBI:36357.definition: Any molecular entity consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:33497.label: transition element molecular entity
CHEBI:33497.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a transition element.

CHEBI:29036.label: copper(2+)
CHEBI:29036.definition: An ion of copper carrying a double positive charge.

CHEBI:18379.label: nitrile
CHEBI:18379.definition: A compound having the structure RC#N; thus a C-substituted derivative of hydrocyanic acid, HC#N. In systematic nomenclature, the suffix nitrile denotes the triply bound #N atom, not the carbon atom attached to it.

CHEBI:38867.label: anaesthetic
CHEBI:38867.definition: Substance which produces loss of feeling or sensation.

CHEBI:35480.label: analgesic
CHEBI:35480.definition: An agent capable of relieving pain without the loss of consciousness or without producing anaesthesia. In addition, analgesic is a role played by a compound which is exhibited by a capability to cause a reduction of pain symptoms.

CHEBI:65265.label: antacid
CHEBI:65265.definition: Any substance which is used to neutralise stomach acidity.

CHEBI:74783.label: astringent
CHEBI:74783.definition: A compound that causes the contraction of body tissues, typically used to reduce bleeding from minor abrasions.

CHEBI:35554.label: cardiovascular drug
CHEBI:35554.definition: A drug that affects the rate or intensity of cardiac contraction, blood vessel diameter or blood volume.

CHEBI:35470.label: central nervous system drug
CHEBI:35470.definition: A class of drugs producing both physiological and psychological effects through a variety of mechanisms involving the central nervous system.

CHEBI:50689.label: reproductive control drug
CHEBI:50689.definition: A substance used either in the prevention or facilitation of pregnancy.

CHEBI:76725.label: EC 1.* (oxidoreductase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76725.definition: An enzyme inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase (EC 1.*.*.*).

CHEBI:76759.label: EC 3.* (hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76759.definition: Any enzyme inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase (EC 3.*.*.*).

CHEBI:76932.label: pathway inhibitor
CHEBI:76932.definition: An enzyme inhibitor that interferes with one or more steps in a metabolic pathway.

CHEBI:33250.label: atom
CHEBI:33250.definition: A chemical entity constituting the smallest component of an element having the chemical properties of the element.

CHEBI:59999.label: chemical substance
CHEBI:59999.definition: A chemical substance is a portion of matter of constant composition, composed of molecular entities of the same type or of different types.

CHEBI:24433.label: group
CHEBI:24433.definition: A defined linked collection of atoms or a single atom within a molecular entity.

CHEBI:23367.label: molecular entity
CHEBI:23367.definition: Any constitutionally or isotopically distinct atom, molecule, ion, ion pair, radical, radical ion, complex, conformer etc., identifiable as a separately distinguishable entity.

CHEBI:52209.label: aetiopathogenetic role
CHEBI:52209.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof which causes the development of a pathological process.

CHEBI:52206.label: biochemical role
CHEBI:52206.definition: A biological role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biochemical context.

CHEBI:35222.label: inhibitor
CHEBI:35222.definition: A substance that diminishes the rate of a chemical reaction.

CHEBI:52210.label: pharmacological role
CHEBI:52210.definition: A biological role which describes how a drug interacts within a biological system and how the interactions affect its medicinal properties.

CHEBI:64909.label: poison
CHEBI:64909.definition: Any substance that causes disturbance to organisms by chemical reaction or other activity on the molecular scale, when a sufficient quantity is absorbed by the organism.

CHEBI:33246.label: inorganic group
CHEBI:33246.definition: Any substituent group which does not contain carbon.

CHEBI:33247.label: organic group
CHEBI:33247.definition: Any substituent group or skeleton containing carbon.

CHEBI:23117.label: chlorine molecular entity
CHEBI:23117.definition: A halogen molecular entity containing one or more atoms of chlorine.

CHEBI:37578.label: halide
CHEBI:37578.definition: Any heteroatomic molecular entity that is a chemical compound of halogen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:24833.label: oxoacid
CHEBI:24833.definition: A compound which contains oxygen, at least one other element, and at least one hydrogen bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

CHEBI:79388.label: divalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79388.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of two.

CHEBI:79389.label: monovalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79389.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of one.

CHEBI:79387.label: trivalent inorganic anion
CHEBI:79387.definition: Any inorganic anion with a valency of three.

CHEBI:24838.label: inorganic phosphate
CHEBI:24838.definition: Any  phosphate that contains no carbon atom.

CHEBI:77635.label: calcium phosphate
CHEBI:77635.definition: A calcium salt composed of calcium and phosphate/diphosphate ions; present in milk and used for the mineralisation of calcified tissues.

CHEBI:63051.label: diammonium hydrogen phosphate
CHEBI:63051.definition: An inorganic phosphate, being the diammonium salt of phosphoric acid.

CHEBI:63036.label: potassium dihydrogen phosphate
CHEBI:63036.definition: A potassium salt in which dihydrogen phosphate(1-) is the counterion.

CHEBI:51336.label: metal sulfate
CHEBI:51336.definition: Sulfate salts where the cation is a metal ion.

CHEBI:22563.label: anion
CHEBI:22563.definition: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the electron.

CHEBI:36916.label: cation
CHEBI:36916.definition: A monoatomic or polyatomic species having one or more elementary charges of the proton.

CHEBI:36358.label: polyatomic ion
CHEBI:36358.definition: An ion consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:75763.label: eukaryotic metabolite
CHEBI:75763.definition: Any  metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in eukaryotes, the taxon that include members of the fungi, plantae and animalia kingdoms.

CHEBI:75787.label: prokaryotic metabolite
CHEBI:75787.definition: Any metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in prokaryotes, the taxon that include members of domains such as the bacteria and archaea.

CHEBI:27026.label: toxin
CHEBI:27026.definition: Poisonous substance produced by a biological organism such as a microbe, animal or plant.

CHEBI:60240.label: divalent metal cation
CHEBI:60240.definition: A metal cation with a valence of two.

CHEBI:38500.label: EC 1.9.3.1 (cytochrome c oxidase) inhibitor
CHEBI:38500.definition: An EC 1.9.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of cytochrome c oxidase (EC 1.9.3.1).

CHEBI:33595.label: cyclic compound
CHEBI:33595.definition: Any molecule that consists of a series of atoms joined together to form a ring.

CHEBI:25362.label: elemental molecule
CHEBI:25362.definition: A molecule all atoms of which have the same atomic number.

CHEBI:72695.label: organic molecule
CHEBI:72695.definition: Any molecule that consists of at least one carbon atom as part of the electrically neutral entity.

CHEBI:29103.label: potassium(1+)
CHEBI:29103.definition: A monoatomic monocation obtained from potassium.

CHEBI:29101.label: sodium(1+)
CHEBI:29101.definition: A monoatomic monocation obtained from sodium.

CHEBI:35604.label: carbon oxoanion
CHEBI:35604.definition: A negative ion consisting solely of carbon and oxygen  atoms, and therefore having the general formula CxOy(n-) for some integers x, y and n.

CHEBI:29067.label: carboxylic acid anion
CHEBI:29067.definition: The conjugate base formed when the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid is deprotonated.

CHEBI:25701.label: organic oxide
CHEBI:25701.definition: An oxide in which the oxygen atom is bonded to a carbon atom.

CHEBI:35406.label: oxoanion
CHEBI:35406.definition: An oxoanion is an anion derived from an oxoacid by loss of hydron(s) bound to oxygen.

CHEBI:24651.label: hydroxides
CHEBI:24651.definition: Hydroxides are chemical compounds containing a hydroxy group or salts containing hydroxide (OH(-)).

CHEBI:36963.label: organooxygen compound
CHEBI:36963.definition: An organochalcogen compound containing at least one carbon-oxygen bond.

CHEBI:25741.label: oxide
CHEBI:25741.definition: An oxide is a chemical compound of oxygen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:26020.label: phosphate
CHEBI:26020.definition: Salts and esters of phosphoric and oligophosphoric acids and their chalcogen analogues. In inorganic chemistry, the term is also used to describe anionic coordination entities with phosphorus as central atom.

CHEBI:6457.label: lignin
CHEBI:6457.definition: A polyphenylpropanoid derived from three monolignol monomers: trans-p-coumaryl alcohol, coniferol and trans-sinapyl alcohol. There is extensive cross-linking and no defined primary structure.

CHEBI:26218.label: potassium salt
CHEBI:26218.definition: Any alkali metal salt having potassium(1+) as the cation.

CHEBI:131526.label: potassium carbonate
CHEBI:131526.definition: A potassium salt that is the dipotassium salt of carbonic acid.

CHEBI:26714.label: sodium salt
CHEBI:26714.definition: Any alkali metal salt having sodium(1+) as the cation.

CHEBI:23004.label: carbamoyl group
CHEBI:23004.definition: The univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of -OH from the carboxy group of carbamic acid.

CHEBI:35176.label: zinc sulfate
CHEBI:35176.definition: A metal sulfate compound having zinc(2+) as the counterion.

CHEBI:63056.label: zinc cation
CHEBI:63056.definition: Any zinc ion that is positively charged.

CHEBI:33256.label: primary amide
CHEBI:33256.definition: A derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

CHEBI:33286.label: agrochemical
CHEBI:33286.definition: An agrochemical is a substance that is used in agriculture or horticulture.

CHEBI:64047.label: food additive
CHEBI:64047.definition: Any substance which is added to food to preserve or enhance its flavour and/or appearance.

CHEBI:25944.label: pesticide
CHEBI:25944.definition: Strictly, a substance intended to kill pests. In common usage, any substance used for controlling, preventing, or destroying animal, microbiological or plant pests.

CHEBI:52217.label: pharmaceutical
CHEBI:52217.definition: Any substance introduced into a living organism with therapeutic or diagnostic purpose.

CHEBI:76414.label: propellant
CHEBI:76414.definition: A compressed gas or liquid with a boiling point lower than room temperature which to used to propel and dispense liquids such as deodorants, insecticides, paints, etc. from aerosol cans.

CHEBI:33893.label: reagent
CHEBI:33893.definition: A substance used in a chemical reaction to detect, measure, examine, or produce other substances.

CHEBI:78433.label: refrigerant
CHEBI:78433.definition: A substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. Refrigerants are used in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and are assigned a "R" number (by ASHRAE - formerly the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers), which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure.

CHEBI:46787.label: solvent
CHEBI:46787.definition: A liquid that can dissolve other substances (solutes) without any change in their chemical composition.

CHEBI:36338.label: lepton
CHEBI:36338.definition: Lepton is a fermion that does not experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek lambdaepsilonpitauomicronsigma (small, thin).

CHEBI:48377.label: imidic acid
CHEBI:48377.definition: Compounds derived from oxoacids RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) by replacing =O by =NR; thus tautomers of amides. In organic chemistry an unspecified imidic acid is generally a carboximidic acid, RC(=NR)(OH).

CHEBI:24632.label: hydrocarbon
CHEBI:24632.definition: A compound consisting of carbon and hydrogen only.

CHEBI:22221.label: acyl group
CHEBI:22221.definition: An organic group formed by removing one or more hydroxy groups from an oxoacid that has the general structure RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0). Although the term is almost always applied to organic compounds, with carboxylic acid as the oxoacid, acyl groups can in principle be derived from other types of acids such as sulfonic acids or phosphonic acids.

CHEBI:33318.label: main group element atom
CHEBI:33318.definition: An atom belonging to one of the main groups (found in the s- and p- blocks) of the periodic table.

CHEBI:33521.label: metal atom
CHEBI:33521.definition: An atom of an element that exhibits typical metallic properties, being typically shiny, with high electrical and thermal conductivity.

CHEBI:137980.label: metalloid atom
CHEBI:137980.definition: An atom of an element that exhibits properties that are between those of metals and nonmetals, or that has a mixture of them. The term generally includes boron, silicon, germanium, arsenic, antimony, and tellurium, while carbon, aluminium, selenium, polonium, and astatine are less commonly included.

CHEBI:37622.label: carboxamide
CHEBI:37622.definition: An amide of a carboxylic acid, having the structure RC(=O)NR2. The term is used as a suffix in systematic name formation to denote the -C(=O)NH2 group including its carbon atom.

CHEBI:33238.label: monoatomic entity
CHEBI:33238.definition: A monoatomic entity is a molecular entity consisting of a single atom.

CHEBI:62488.label: signalling molecule
CHEBI:62488.definition: A molecular messenger in which the molecule is specifically involved in transmitting information between cells. Such molecules are released from the cell sending the signal, cross over the gap between cells by diffusion, and interact with specific receptors in another cell, triggering a response in that cell by activating a series of enzyme controlled reactions which lead to changes inside the cell.

CHEBI:27027.label: micronutrient
CHEBI:27027.definition: Any nutrient required in small quantities by organisms throughout their life in order to orchestrate a range of physiological functions.

CHEBI:36962.label: organochalcogen compound
CHEBI:36962.definition: An organochalcogen compound is a compound containing at least one carbon-chalcogen bond.

CHEBI:35352.label: organonitrogen compound
CHEBI:35352.definition: Any heteroorganic entity containing at least one carbon-nitrogen bond.

CHEBI:33287.label: fertilizer
CHEBI:33287.definition: A fertilizer is any substance that is added to soil or water to assist the growth of plants.

CHEBI:33560.label: p-block element atom
CHEBI:33560.definition: Any main group element atom belonging to the p-block of the periodic table.

CHEBI:30563.label: silicon dioxide
CHEBI:30563.definition: A silicon oxide made up of linear triatomic molecules in which a silicon atom is covalently bonded to two oxygens.

CHEBI:18248.label: iron atom
CHEBI:18248.definition: An iron group element atom that has atomic number 26.

CHEBI:26836.label: sulfuric acid
CHEBI:26836.definition: A sulfur oxoacid that consists of two oxo and two hydroxy groups joined covalently to a central sulfur atom.

CHEBI:18407.label: hydrogen cyanide
CHEBI:18407.definition: A one-carbon compound consisting of a methine group triple bonded to a nitrogen atom

CHEBI:33457.label: phosphorus oxoacid
CHEBI:33457.definition: A pnictogen oxoacid which contains phosphorus and oxygen, at least one hydrogen atom bound to oxygen, and forms an ion by the loss of one or more protons.

CHEBI:16042.label: halide anion
CHEBI:16042.definition: A monoatomic monoanion resulting from the addition of an electron to any halogen atom.

CHEBI:48107.label: nitric acid
CHEBI:48107.definition: A nitrogen oxoacid of formula HNO3 in which the nitrogen atom is bonded to a hydroxy group and by equivalent bonds to the remaining two oxygen atoms.

CHEBI:59698.label: phosphoric acids
CHEBI:59698.definition: Compounds containing one or more phosphoric acid units.

CHEBI:17632.label: nitrate
CHEBI:17632.definition: A nitrogen oxoanion formed by loss of a proton from nitric acid. Principal species present at pH 7.3.

CHEBI:35780.label: phosphate ion
CHEBI:35780.definition: A phosphorus oxoanion that is the conjugate base of phosphoric acid.

CHEBI:16189.label: sulfate
CHEBI:16189.definition: A sulfur oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of both OH groups of sulfuric acid.

CHEBI:15075.label: selenate
CHEBI:15075.definition: A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from selenic acid.

CHEBI:33676.label: d-block molecular entity
CHEBI:33676.definition: A d-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of a d-block element.

CHEBI:88184.label: metal allergen
CHEBI:88184.definition: Any metal which causes the onset of an allergic reaction.

CHEBI:27081.label: transition element atom
CHEBI:27081.definition: An element whose atom has an incomplete d sub-shell, or which can give rise to cations with an incomplete d sub-shell.

CHEBI:33303.label: chalcogen
CHEBI:33303.definition: Any p-block element belonging to the group 16 family of the periodic table.

CHEBI:33300.label: pnictogen
CHEBI:33300.definition: Any p-block element atom that is in group 15 of the periodic table: nitrogen, phosphorus, arsenic, antimony and bismuth.

CHEBI:33709.label: amino acid
CHEBI:33709.definition: A carboxylic acid containing one or more amino groups.

CHEBI:138675.label: gas molecular entity
CHEBI:138675.definition: Any main group molecular entity that is gaseous at standard temperature and pressure (STP; 0degreeC and 100 kPa).

CHEBI:33583.label: noble gas molecular entity
CHEBI:33583.definition: A main group molecular entity containing one or more atoms of any noble gas.

CHEBI:33675.label: p-block molecular entity
CHEBI:33675.definition: A main group molecular entity that contains one or more atoms of a p-block element.

CHEBI:33674.label: s-block molecular entity
CHEBI:33674.definition: An s-block molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an s-block element.

CHEBI:50860.label: organic molecular entity
CHEBI:50860.definition: Any molecular entity that contains carbon.

CHEBI:33655.label: aromatic compound
CHEBI:33655.definition: A cyclically conjugated molecular entity with a stability (due to delocalization) significantly greater than that of a hypothetical localized structure (e.g. Kekule structure) is said to possess aromatic character.

CHEBI:33832.label: organic cyclic compound
CHEBI:33832.definition: Any organic molecule that consists of atoms connected in the form of a ring.

CHEBI:33405.label: hydracid
CHEBI:33405.definition: A hydracid is a compound which contains hydrogen that is not bound to oxygen, and which produces a conjugate base by loss of positive hydrogen ion(s) (hydrons).

CHEBI:33692.label: hydrides
CHEBI:33692.definition: Hydrides are chemical compounds of hydrogen with other chemical elements.

CHEBI:26004.label: phenylpropanoid
CHEBI:26004.definition: Any organic aromatic compound with a structure based on a phenylpropane skeleton. The class includes naturally occurring phenylpropanoid esters, flavonoids, anthocyanins, coumarins and many small phenolic molecules as well as their semi-synthetic and synthetic analogues. Phenylpropanoids are also precursors of lignin.

CHEBI:33296.label: alkali metal molecular entity
CHEBI:33296.definition: A molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkali metal.

CHEBI:33299.label: alkaline earth molecular entity
CHEBI:33299.definition: An alkaline earth molecular entity is a molecular entity containing one or more atoms of an alkaline earth metal.

CHEBI:33304.label: chalcogen molecular entity
CHEBI:33304.definition: Any p-block molecular entity containing a chalcogen.

CHEBI:33302.label: pnictogen molecular entity
CHEBI:33302.definition: A p-block molecular entity containing any pnictogen.

CHEBI:15377.label: water
CHEBI:15377.definition: An oxygen hydride consisting of an oxygen atom that is covalently bonded to two hydrogen atoms.

CHEBI:35274.label: ammonium ion derivative
CHEBI:35274.definition: A derivative of ammonium, NH4(+), in which one (or more) of the hydrogens bonded to the nitrogen have been replaced with univalent organyl groups. The substituting carbon of the organyl group must not itself be directly attached to a heteroatom (thereby excluding protonated amides, hemiaminals, etc).

CHEBI:33694.label: biomacromolecule
CHEBI:33694.definition: A macromolecule formed by a living organism.

CHEBI:132717.label: bleaching agent
CHEBI:132717.definition: A reagent that lightens or whitens a substrate through chemical reaction. Bleaching reactions usually involve oxidative or reductive processes that degrade colour systems. Bleaching can occur by destroying one or more of the double bonds in the conjugated chain, by cleaving the conjugated chain, or by oxidation of one of the other moieties in the conjugated chain. Their reactivity results in many bleaches having strong bactericidal, disinfecting, and sterilising properties.

CHEBI:59740.label: nucleophilic reagent
CHEBI:59740.definition: A reagent that forms a bond to its reaction partner (the electrophile) by donating both bonding electrons.

CHEBI:64736.label: magnesium nitrate
CHEBI:64736.definition: The inorganic nitrate salt of magnesium.

CHEBI:32599.label: magnesium sulfate
CHEBI:32599.definition: A magnesium salt having sulfate as the counterion.

CHEBI:28938.label: ammonium
CHEBI:28938.definition: An onium cation obtained by protonation of ammonia.

CHEBI:35107.label: azane
CHEBI:35107.definition: Saturated acyclic nitrogen hydrides having the general formula NnHn+2.

CHEBI:29340.label: hydridonitrate(2-)
CHEBI:29340.definition: A divalent inorganic anion resulting from the removal of two protons from ammonia.

CHEBI:23924.label: enzyme inhibitor
CHEBI:23924.definition: A compound or agent that combines with an enzyme in such a manner as to prevent the normal substrate-enzyme combination and the catalytic reaction.

CHEBI:28616.label: carbamic acid
CHEBI:28616.definition: A one-carbon compound that is ammonia in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group. Although carbamic acid derivatives are common, carbamic acid itself has never been synthesised.

CHEBI:23424.label: cyanides
CHEBI:23424.definition: Salts and C-organyl derivatives of hydrogen cyanide, HC#N.

CHEBI:50047.label: organic amino compound
CHEBI:50047.definition: A compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by organyl groups.

CHEBI:35488.label: central nervous system depressant
CHEBI:35488.definition: A loosely defined group of drugs that tend to reduce the activity of the central nervous system.

CHEBI:35623.label: anticonvulsant
CHEBI:35623.definition: A drug used to prevent seizures or reduce their severity.

CHEBI:35505.label: hydrate
CHEBI:35505.definition: An addition compound that contains water in weak chemical combination with another compound.

CHEBI:38070.label: anti-arrhythmia drug
CHEBI:38070.definition: A drug used for the treatment or prevention of cardiac arrhythmias. Anti-arrhythmia drugs may affect the polarisation-repolarisation phase of the action potential, its excitability or refractoriness, or impulse conduction or membrane responsiveness within cardiac fibres.

CHEBI:35620.label: vasodilator agent
CHEBI:35620.definition: A drug used to cause dilation of the blood vessels.

CHEBI:17544.label: hydrogencarbonate
CHEBI:17544.definition: The carbon oxoanion resulting from the removal of a proton from carbonic acid.

CHEBI:33575.label: carboxylic acid
CHEBI:33575.definition: A carbon oxoacid acid carrying at least one -C(=O)OH group and having the structure RC(=O)OH, where R is any any monovalent functional group. Carboxylic acids are the most common type of organic acid.

CHEBI:39745.label: dihydrogenphosphate
CHEBI:39745.definition: A monovalent inorganic anion that consists of phosphoric acid in which one of the three OH groups has been deprotonated.

CHEBI:43474.label: hydrogenphosphate
CHEBI:43474.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of dihydrogenphosphate.

CHEBI:18367.label: phosphate(3-)
CHEBI:18367.definition: A phosphate ion that is the conjugate base of hydrogenphosphate.

CHEBI:26710.label: sodium chloride
CHEBI:26710.definition: An inorganic chloride salt having sodium(1+) as the counterion.

CHEBI:10545.label: electron
CHEBI:10545.definition: Elementary particle not affected by the strong force having a spin 1/2, a negative elementary charge and a rest mass of 0.000548579903(13) u, or 0.51099906(15) MeV.

CHEBI:33253.label: nucleon
CHEBI:33253.definition: Heavy nuclear particle: proton or neutron.

CHEBI:36339.label: baryon
CHEBI:36339.definition: Baryon is a fermion that does experience the strong force (strong interaction). The term is derived from the Greek betaalpharhoupsilonsigma (heavy).

CHEBI:36343.label: composite particle
CHEBI:36343.definition: A subatomic particle known to have substructure (i.e. consisting of smaller particles).

CHEBI:36340.label: fermion
CHEBI:36340.definition: Particle of half-integer spin quantum number following Fermi-Dirac statistics. Fermions are named after Enrico Fermi.

CHEBI:33233.label: fundamental particle
CHEBI:33233.definition: A particle not known to have substructure.

CHEBI:36347.label: nuclear particle
CHEBI:36347.definition: A nucleus or any of its constituents in any of their energy states.

CHEBI:36344.label: hadron
CHEBI:36344.definition: Hadron is a subatomic particle which experiences the strong force.

CHEBI:33252.label: atomic nucleus
CHEBI:33252.definition: A nucleus is the positively charged central portion of an atom, excluding the orbital electrons.

CHEBI:37577.label: heteroatomic molecular entity
CHEBI:37577.definition: A molecular entity consisting of two or more chemical elements.

CHEBI:33839.label: macromolecule
CHEBI:33839.definition: A macromolecule is a molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

CHEBI:25367.label: molecule
CHEBI:25367.definition: Any polyatomic entity that is an electrically neutral entity consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:33702.label: polyatomic cation
CHEBI:33702.definition: A cation consisting of more than one atom.

CHEBI:36586.label: carbonyl compound
CHEBI:36586.definition: Any compound containing the carbonyl group, C=O. The term is commonly used in the restricted sense of aldehydes and ketones, although it actually includes carboxylic acids and derivatives.

CHEBI:17514.label: cyanide
CHEBI:17514.definition: A pseudohalide anion that is the conjugate base of hydrogen cyanide.

CHEBI:64641.label: divalent inorganic cation
CHEBI:64641.definition: An inorganic cation with a valency of two.

CHEBI:60242.label: monovalent inorganic cation
CHEBI:60242.definition: An atom or small molecule with a positive charge that does not contain carbon in covalent linkage, with a valency of one.

CHEBI:23016.label: carbonates
CHEBI:23016.definition: Organooxygen compounds that are salts or esters of carbonic acid, H2CO3.

CHEBI:33245.label: organic fundamental parent
CHEBI:33245.definition: An organic fundamental parent is a structure used as a basis for substitutive names in organic nomenclature, containing, in addition to one or more hydrogen atoms, a single atom of an element, a number of atoms (alike or different) linked together to form an unbranched chain, a monocyclic or polycyclic ring system, or a ring assembly or ring/chain system.

CHEBI:35504.label: addition compound
CHEBI:35504.definition: An addition compound contains two or more simpler compounds that can be packed in a definite ratio into a crystal. The term covers donor-acceptor complexes (adducts) and a variety of lattice compounds.

CHEBI:24866.label: salt
CHEBI:24866.definition: A salt is an assembly of cations and anions.

CHEBI:29347.label: monocarboxylic acid amide
CHEBI:29347.definition: A carboxamide derived from a monocarboxylic acid.

CHEBI:26820.label: sulfates
CHEBI:26820.definition: Salts and esters of sulfuric acid

CHEBI:27207.label: univalent carboacyl group
CHEBI:27207.definition: A univalent carboacyl group is a group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of a carboxylic acid.

CHEBI:38808.label: calcium channel modulator
CHEBI:38808.definition: A membrane transport modulator that is able to regulate intracellular calcium levels.

CHEBI:38215.label: calcium channel blocker
CHEBI:38215.definition: One of a class of drugs that acts by selective inhibition of calcium influx through cell membranes or on the release and binding of calcium in intracellular pools.

CHEBI:138103.label: inorganic acid
CHEBI:138103.definition: A Bronsted acid derived from one or more inorganic compounds. Inorganic acids (also known as mineral acids) form hydrons and conjugate base ions when dissolved in water.

CHEBI:48356.label: protic solvent
CHEBI:48356.definition: A polar solvent that is capable of acting as a hydron (proton) donor.

CHEBI:48354.label: polar solvent
CHEBI:48354.definition: A solvent that is composed of polar molecules. Polar solvents can dissolve ionic compounds or ionisable covalent compounds.

CHEBI:62982.label: ammonium dihydrogen phosphate
CHEBI:62982.definition: The ammonium salt of phosphoric acid (molar ratio 1:1).

CHEBI:48379.label: isourea
CHEBI:48379.definition: A carboximidic acid that is the imidic acid tautomer of urea, H2NC(=NH)OH, and its hydrocarbyl derivatives.

CHEBI:50313.label: onium cation
CHEBI:50313.definition: Mononuclear cations derived by addition of a hydron to a mononuclear parent hydride of the pnictogen, chalcogen and halogen families.

CHEBI:64302.label: cyanamide(2-)
CHEBI:64302.definition: An organic nitrogen anion formed from cyanamide by loss of its two protons.

CHEBI:66993.label: tocolytic agent
CHEBI:66993.definition: Any compound used to suppress premature labour and immature birth by suppressing uterine contractions.

CHEBI:33285.label: heteroorganic entity
CHEBI:33285.definition: A heteroorganic entity is an organic molecular entity in which carbon atoms or organic groups are bonded directly to one or more heteroatoms.

CHEBI:64708.label: one-carbon compound
CHEBI:64708.definition: An organic molecular entity containing a single carbon atom (C1).

CHEBI:64709.label: organic acid
CHEBI:64709.definition: Any organic molecular entity that is acidic and contains carbon in covalent linkage.

CHEBI:33232.label: application
CHEBI:33232.definition: Intended use of the molecular entity or part thereof by humans.

CHEBI:24432.label: biological role
CHEBI:24432.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a biological context.

CHEBI:51086.label: chemical role
CHEBI:51086.definition: A role played by the molecular entity or part thereof within a chemical context.

CHEBI:15339.label: acceptor
CHEBI:15339.definition: A molecular entity that can accept an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group from another molecular entity.

CHEBI:37527.label: acid
CHEBI:37527.definition: An acid is a molecular entity capable of donating a hydron (Bronsted acid) or capable of forming a covalent bond with an electron pair (Lewis acid).

CHEBI:22695.label: base
CHEBI:22695.definition: A molecular entity having an available pair of electrons capable of forming a covalent bond with a hydron (Bronsted base) or with the vacant orbital of some other molecular entity (Lewis base).

CHEBI:35223.label: catalyst
CHEBI:35223.definition: A substance that increases the rate of a reaction without modifying the overall standard Gibbs energy change in the reaction.

CHEBI:17891.label: donor
CHEBI:17891.definition: A molecular entity that can transfer ("donate") an electron, a pair of electrons, an atom or a group to another molecular entity.

CHEBI:63490.label: explosive
CHEBI:63490.definition: A substance capable of undergoing rapid and highly exothermic decomposition.

CHEBI:76413.label: greenhouse gas
CHEBI:76413.definition: A gas in an atmosphere that absorbs and emits radiation within the thermal infrared range, so contributing to the 'greenhouse effect'.

CHEBI:63248.label: oxidising agent
CHEBI:63248.definition: A substance that removes electrons from another reactant in a redox reaction.

CHEBI:32988.label: amide
CHEBI:32988.definition: An amide is a derivative of an oxoacid RkE(=O)l(OH)m (l =/= 0) in which an acidic hydroxy group has been replaced by an amino or substituted amino group.

CHEBI:35276.label: ammonium compound
CHEBI:35276.definition: Compounds (NH4(+))Y(-) and derivatives, in which one or more of the hydrogens bonded to nitrogen have been replaced with univalent groups.

CHEBI:62764.label: reactive nitrogen species
CHEBI:62764.definition: A family of nitrogen molecular entities which are highly reactive and derived from nitric oxide (.NO) and superoxide (O2.(-)) produced via the enzymatic activity of inducible nitric oxide synthase 2 (NOS2) and NADPH oxidase respectively.

CHEBI:23414.label: copper(II) sulfate
CHEBI:23414.definition: A metal sulfate compound having copper(2+) as the metal ion.

CHEBI:51422.label: organodiyl group
CHEBI:51422.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having two free valences at carbon atom(s).

CHEBI:33249.label: organyl group
CHEBI:33249.definition: Any organic substituent group, regardless of functional type, having one free valence at a carbon atom.

CHEBI:23357.label: cofactor
CHEBI:23357.definition: An organic molecule or ion (usually a metal ion) that is required by an enzyme for its activity. It may be attached either loosely (coenzyme) or tightly (prosthetic group).

CHEBI:25212.label: metabolite
CHEBI:25212.definition: Any intermediate or product resulting from metabolism. The term 'metabolite' subsumes the classes commonly known as primary and secondary metabolites.

CHEBI:38632.label: membrane transport modulator
CHEBI:38632.definition: Any agent that affects the transport of molecular entities across a biological membrane.

CHEBI:50904.label: allergen
CHEBI:50904.definition: A chemical compound, or part thereof, which causes the onset of an allergic reaction by interacting with any of the molecular pathways involved in an allergy.

CHEBI:50902.label: genotoxin
CHEBI:50902.definition: A role played by a chemical compound to induce direct or indirect DNA damage. Such damage can potentially lead to the formation of a malignant tumour, but DNA damage does not lead inevitably to the creation of cancerous cells.

CHEBI:50910.label: neurotoxin
CHEBI:50910.definition: A poison that interferes with the functions of the nervous system.

CHEBI:139492.label: sensitiser
CHEBI:139492.definition: A chemical compound that causes a substantial proportion of exposed people or animals to develop an allergic reaction in normal tissue after repeated exposure to the compound.

CHEBI:33290.label: food
CHEBI:33290.definition: Any material that can be ingested by an organism.

CHEBI:78295.label: food component
CHEBI:78295.definition: Any substance that is distributed in foodstuffs. It includes materials derived from plants or animals, such as vitamins or minerals, as well as environmental contaminants.

CHEBI:23888.label: drug
CHEBI:23888.definition: Any substance which when absorbed into a living organism may modify one or more of its functions. The term is generally accepted for a substance taken for a therapeutic purpose, but is also commonly used for abused substances.

CHEBI:18219.label: ammonium hydroxide
CHEBI:18219.definition: A solution of ammonia in water.

CHEBI:46662.label: mineral
CHEBI:46662.definition: In general, a mineral is a chemical substance that is normally crystalline formed and has been formed as a result of geological processes. The term also includes metamict substances (naturally occurring, formerly crystalline substances whose crystallinity has been destroyed by ionising radiation) and can include naturally occurring amorphous substances that have never been crystalline ('mineraloids') such as georgite and calciouranoite as well as substances formed by the action of geological processes on bigenic compounds ('biogenic minerals').

CHEBI:60004.label: mixture
CHEBI:60004.definition: A mixture is a chemical substance composed of multiple molecules, at least two of which are of a different kind.

CHEBI:64577.label: flour treatment agent
CHEBI:64577.definition: A food additive which is added to flour or dough to improve baking quality and/or colour.

CHEBI:64049.label: food acidity regulator
CHEBI:64049.definition: A food additive that is used to change or otherwise control the acidity or alkalinity of foods. They may be acids, bases, neutralising agents or buffering agents.

CHEBI:77182.label: food colouring
CHEBI:77182.definition: A food additive that imparts colour to food. In European countries, E-numbers for permitted food colours are from E 100 to E 199, divided into yellows (E 100-109), oranges (E 110-119), reds (E 120-129), blues and violets (E 130-139), greens (E 140-149), browns and blacks (E 150-159), and others (E 160-199).

CHEBI:77960.label: food firming agent
CHEBI:77960.definition: A food additive that is used to make or keep fruit or vegetable tissues firm and crisp. or which interacts with gelling agents such as pectin to produce or strengthen a gel.

CHEBI:77974.label: food packaging gas
CHEBI:77974.definition: A food additive that is a (generally inert) gas which is used to envelop foodstuffs during packing and so protect them from unwanted chemical reactions such as food spoilage or oxidation during subsequent transport and storage. The term includes propellant gases, used to expel foods from a container.

CHEBI:78017.label: food propellant
CHEBI:78017.definition: A propellant that is used to expel foods from an aerosol container.

CHEBI:36587.label: organic oxo compound
CHEBI:36587.definition: Organic compounds containing an oxygen atom, =O, doubly bonded to carbon or another element.

CHEBI:84735.label: algal metabolite
CHEBI:84735.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in algae including unicellular organisms like chlorella and diatoms to multicellular organisms like giant kelps and brown algae.

CHEBI:75767.label: animal metabolite
CHEBI:75767.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in animals that include diverse creatures from sponges, insects to mammals.

CHEBI:76946.label: fungal metabolite
CHEBI:76946.definition: Any eukaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in fungi, the kingdom that includes microorganisms such as the yeasts and moulds.

CHEBI:83039.label: crustacean metabolite
CHEBI:83039.definition: An animal metabolite produced by arthropods such as crabs, lobsters, crayfish, shrimps and krill.

CHEBI:75768.label: mammalian metabolite
CHEBI:75768.definition: Any animal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in mammals.

CHEBI:77746.label: human metabolite
CHEBI:77746.definition: Any mammalian metabolite  produced during a metabolic reaction in humans (Homo sapiens).

CHEBI:75771.label: mouse metabolite
CHEBI:75771.definition: Any mammalian metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in a mouse (Mus musculus).

CHEBI:76969.label: bacterial metabolite
CHEBI:76969.definition: Any prokaryotic metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in bacteria.

CHEBI:76727.label: EC 1.2.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor aldehyde/oxo group) inhibitor
CHEBI:76727.definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors (EC 1.2.*.*).

CHEBI:76736.label: EC 1.9.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group) inhibitor
CHEBI:76736.definition: An oxidoreductase inhibitor which interferes with the action of an oxidoreductase acting on a heme group of donors (EC 1.9.*.*).

CHEBI:76852.label: EC 1.2.1.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor aldehyde/oxo group with NAD(+) or NADP(+) as acceptor) inhibitor
CHEBI:76852.definition: An EC 1.2.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor aldehyde/oxo group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme using NAD(+) or NADP(+) as acceptor (EC 1.2.1.*).

CHEBI:76870.label: EC 1.9.3.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group, oxygen as acceptor) inhibitor
CHEBI:76870.definition: An EC 1.9.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor heme group) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any such enzyme using oxygen as acceptor (EC 1.9.3.*).

CHEBI:76760.label: EC 3.1.* (ester hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76760.definition: A hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of any ester hydrolase (EC 3.1.*.*).

CHEBI:76764.label: EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor
CHEBI:76764.definition: Any hydrolase inhibitor that interferes with the action of a hydrolase acting on C-N bonds, other than peptide bonds (EC 3.5.*.*).

CHEBI:76775.label: EC 3.1.3.* (phosphoric monoester hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76775.definition: An EC 3.1.* (ester hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any phosphoric monoester hydrolase (EC 3.1.3.*).

CHEBI:76807.label: EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor
CHEBI:76807.definition: An EC 3.5.* (hydrolases acting on non-peptide C-N bonds) inhibitor that interferes with the action of any non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase (EC 3.5.1.*).

CHEBI:35608.label: EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor
CHEBI:35608.definition: An EC 3.1.3.* (phosphoric monoester hydrolase) inhibitor which interferes with the activity of the enzyme protein tyrosine phosphatases (PTPs), EC 3.1.3.48, involved in the removal of phosphate groups from phosphorylated tyrosine residues on proteins.

CHEBI:77941.label: EC 3.5.1.4 (amidase) inhibitor
CHEBI:77941.definition: An EC 3.5.1.* (non-peptide linear amide C-N hydrolase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of amidase (EC 3.5.1.4).

CHEBI:35487.label: EC 1.2.1.3 [aldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD(+))] inhibitor
CHEBI:35487.definition: An EC 1.2.1.* (oxidoreductase acting on donor aldehyde/oxo group with NAD(+) or NADP(+) as acceptor) inhibitor that interferes with the action of aldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD(+)), EC 1.2.1.3.

CHEBI:75772.label: Saccharomyces cerevisiae metabolite
CHEBI:75772.definition: Any  fungal metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Baker's yeast (Saccharomyces cerevisiae).

CHEBI:76971.label: Escherichia coli metabolite
CHEBI:76971.definition: Any bacterial metabolite produced during a metabolic reaction in Escherichia coli.

CHEBI:33284.label: nutrient
CHEBI:33284.definition: A nutrient is a food component that an organism uses to survive and grow.

CHEBI:15138.label: sulfide(2-)
CHEBI:15138.definition: A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from hydrogen sulfide.

CHEBI:83057.label: Daphnia metabolite
CHEBI:83057.definition: A crustacean metabolite produced by the genus of small planktonic arthropods, Daphnia

CHEBI:83056.label: Daphnia magna metabolite
CHEBI:83056.definition: A Daphnia metabolite produced by the species Daphnia magna.

ENVO:00000002.label: anthropogenic geographic feature
ENVO:00000002.definition: An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

ENVO:00000012.label: hydrographic feature
ENVO:00000012.definition: A geographical feature associated with water.

ENVO:00000098.label: island
ENVO:00000098.definition: Area of dry or relatively dry land surrounded by water or low wetland.

ENVO:01000281.label: layer
ENVO:01000281.definition: A layer is a quantity of some material which is spatially continuous, has comparable thickness, and usually covers some surface.

ENVO:00000070.label: construction
ENVO:00000070.definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

ENVO:00000046.label: hedge
ENVO:00000046.definition: A dense growth of shrubbery planted as a fence or boundary.

ENVO:00000026.label: well
ENVO:00000026.definition: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

ENVO:00000005.label: first-order administrative region
ENVO:00000005.definition: A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.

ENVO:00000123.label: political entity
ENVO:00000123.definition: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.

ENVO:00000006.label: second-order administrative region
ENVO:00000006.definition: A subdivision of a first-order administrative division.

ENVO:00000007.label: third-order administrative region
ENVO:00000007.definition: A subdivision of a second-order administrative division.

ENVO:00000475.label: inlet
ENVO:00000475.definition: An opening of the sea into the land, or of a lake into its shore.

ENVO:00000093.label: lacustrine beach
ENVO:00000093.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a lake.

ENVO:00000178.label: levee
ENVO:00000178.definition: An artificial slope or wall, usually earthen, which parallels the course of a river, built for the purpose of containing the river.

ENVO:01000044.label: marine pelagic feature
ENVO:01000044.definition: A prominent or distinctive aspect, quality, or characteristic of environments occurring within the marine water column.

ENVO:00000130.label: rocky reef
ENVO:00000130.definition: A ridge of rocks, lying near the surface of the sea, which may be visible at low tide, but is usually covered by water.

ENVO:00000017.label: saline hydrographic feature
ENVO:00000017.definition: A geographical feature associated with water with a halinity above 30 ppt (roughly 35 g/L).

ENVO:00000304.label: shore
ENVO:00000304.definition: That part of the land in immediate contact with a body of water including the area between high and low water lines.

ENVO:00000501.label: submerged bed
ENVO:00000501.definition: The portion of the ground surface which lies below water.

ENVO:00000092.label: sea beach
ENVO:00000092.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a sea.

ENVO:00000019.label: saline lake
ENVO:00000019.definition: A lake whose water contains a considerable concentration of dissolved salts.

ENVO:01001062.label: crater lake
ENVO:01001062.definition: A lake contained within a crater.

ENVO:01001022.label: natural lake
ENVO:01001022.definition: A lake which has formed as the result of processes that are not or are only minimally driven by human activity.

ENVO:01000297.label: freshwater river
ENVO:01000297.definition: A river where fresh water flows.

ENVO:00000450.label: irrigation reservoir
ENVO:00000450.definition: A reservoir constructed for the purpose of providing water for irrigation.

ENVO:00000023.label: stream
ENVO:00000023.definition: A watercourse which is linear and flows across the solid portion of a planetary surface.

ENVO:01000710.label: flood
ENVO:01000710.definition: An unusual accumulation of water above the ground caused by high tide, heavy rain, melting snow or rapid runoff from paved areas.

ENVO:01001320.label: fresh water body
ENVO:01001320.definition: A body of water which is primarily composed of freshwater, with low solute content.

AGRO:00000009.label: irrigation source
AGRO:00000009.definition: A water body from which water is taken during an irrigation process and transported to the target of the irrigation process.

ENVO:01000617.label: lentic water body
ENVO:01000617.definition: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

ENVO:01000618.label: lotic water body
ENVO:01000618.definition: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

ENVO:01001319.label: saline water body
ENVO:01001319.definition: A body of water which is primarily composed of saline water.

AGRO:00000391.label: field margin
AGRO:00000391.definition:
Strips of land along the borders of crop fields. It also include vegetative strips adjacent
to roads, paths, railways, hedgerows and forest boundaries.

ENVO:00000090.label: coastal plain
ENVO:00000090.definition: An area of flat, low-lying land adjacent to a coast and separated from the interior by other features.

ENVO:00000255.label: flood plain
ENVO:00000255.definition: An area which is subject to periodic flooding.

ENVO:00000312.label: sandur
ENVO:00000312.definition: The plain formed by the large amounts of silt and sediment, picked up as a glacier erodes the underlying rocks as it moves slowly downhill, and at the snout of the glacier, meltwater can carry this sediment away from the glacier and deposit it on a broad plain. The material in the outwash plain is often size-sorted by the water runoff of the melting glacier with the finest materials, like silt, being the most distantly re-deposited, whereas larger boulders are the closest to the original terminus of the glacier.

ENVO:00000222.label: oceanic island
ENVO:00000222.definition: An island that does not sit on a continental shelf, and is of volcanic origin.

ENVO:00000247.label: volcano
ENVO:00000247.definition: An opening, or rupture, in the Earth's surface or crust, which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

ENVO:00000424.label: lake island
ENVO:00000424.definition: An island that lies in a lake.

ENVO:00000423.label: river island
ENVO:00000423.definition: An island that lies in a river.

ENVO:00000128.label: dry valley
ENVO:00000128.definition: A valley that no longer has a surface flow of water. Typically found in either Karst (limestone) or chalk terrain.

ENVO:00000248.label: glacial valley
ENVO:00000248.definition: A valley that contains, or contained, a glacier and was formed by glacial activity. Typically U-shaped in cross-section.

ENVO:00000129.label: stream valley
ENVO:00000129.definition: A valley that contains, and has been formed by, a stream.

ENVO:00000266.label: pasture
ENVO:00000266.definition: A grassland ecosystem which is used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

ENVO:00000260.label: prairie
ENVO:00000260.definition: An area of land of low topographic relief that historically supported grasses and herbs, with few trees, and having generally a mesic (moderate or temperate) climate. Dominated by tall grasses (contrast steppe).

ENVO:00000261.label: savanna
ENVO:00000261.definition: A grassland of the tropics or subtropics with scattered trees.

ENVO:00000262.label: steppe
ENVO:00000262.definition: A plain without trees (apart from those near rivers and lakes); it is similar to a prairie, although a prairie is generally considered as being dominated by tall grasses, while short grasses are said to be normal in the steppe. It may be semi-desert, or covered with grass or shrubs or both, depending on the season and latitude.

ENVO:01000888.label: area of gramanoid or herbaceous vegetation
ENVO:01000888.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by gramanoid or herbaceous vegetation and which is not subject to intensive management by humans. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:00000111.label: forested area
ENVO:00000111.definition: An area with a high density of trees. A small forest may be called a wood.

ENVO:00000297.label: paddy field
ENVO:00000297.definition: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.

AGRO:00000390.label: fallow land
AGRO:00000390.definition: An agricultural field that is set aside for a period of time before it is cultivated again; or an agricultral field that is under permanent crops, meadows or pastures and that is not being used for such purposes for a period of at least one year.

ENVO:00000009.label: national geopolitical entity
ENVO:00000009.definition: A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.

ENVO:01000818.label: cryosphere
ENVO:01000818.definition: A cryosphere is that part of a planet which is primarily composed of water is in solid form.

ENVO:01001276.label: water ice layer
ENVO:01001276.definition: A layer which is primarily composed of some solid material, allowing for non-solid parts such as interstitial pockets of gas or liquid.

ENVO:00000393.label: sound
ENVO:00000393.definition: A large sea or ocean inlet larger than a bay, deeper than a bight, wider than a fjord, or it may identify a narrow sea or ocean channel between two bodies of land.

ENVO:00000142.label: stream bank
ENVO:00000142.definition: The sloping margin of a stream, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000143.label: river bank
ENVO:00000143.definition: The sloping margin of a river, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000542.label: kame
ENVO:00000542.definition: An irregularly shaped hill or mound composed of sorted or stratified sand and gravel that is deposited in contact with the glacial ice. It can have an irregular shape. Kames are often associated with kettles, and this is referred to as kame and kettle topography. When the ice retreats further, the delta kame often collapses. Kame terraces are frequently found along the side of a glacial valley and are the deposits of meltwater streams flowing between the ice and the adjacent valley side.

ENVO:01001491.label: flattened elevation
ENVO:01001491.definition: An elevation which is flattened across its highest surface.

ENVO:00000176.label: elevation
ENVO:00000176.definition: A landform elevated above the surrounding area.

ENVO:00000508.label: terrace
ENVO:00000508.definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

AGRO:00000339.label: agronomic land element
AGRO:00000339.definition: Description of the geomorphology of the immediate surroundings of the experimental site.

ENVO:03000110.label: cryoform
ENVO:03000110.definition: A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous mass of snow and/or ice.

ENVO:01000667.label: geological fracture
ENVO:01000667.definition: A geological fracture is any separation in a geologic formation, such as a joint or a fault that divides a mass of rock into two or more pieces.

AGRO:00000338.label: higher-level landform
AGRO:00000338.definition: The landform refers to the shape of the land surface in the area in which the agronomic trial site is located.

ENVO:01001275.label: solid layer
ENVO:01001275.definition: A layer which is primarily composed of some solid material, allowing for non-solid parts such as interstitial pockets of gas or liquid.

ENVO:01001097.label: tectonic plate
ENVO:01001097.definition: A part of a lithosphere which is separated by other such parts by geographic faults or similar geomorphological discontinuities.

ENVO:00000166.label: atoll
ENVO:00000166.definition: An oceanic island, often having a characteristic ring-like shape surrounding a lagoon. Atolls are formed when coral reef grows around a volcanic island that later subsides into the ocean.

ENVO:01000328.label: dome swamp
ENVO:01000328.definition: A dome swamp is a swamp which occurs in a depression where deeper waters at the centre of the swamp allow  trees to grow taller relative to those in shallower regions of the depression. This creates a dome-like shape.

ENVO:00000184.label: hanging valley
ENVO:00000184.definition: A tributary valley with the floor at a higher relief than the main channel into which it flows. They are most commonly associated with U-shaped valleys when a tributary glacier flows into a glacier of larger volume.

ENVO:00000529.label: beach ridge
ENVO:00000529.definition: A ridge of sand just inland and parallel to the beach, usually in series.

ENVO:01000237.label: coastal scrubland
ENVO:01000237.definition: A coastal scrubland is a scrubland which is part of a coast.

ENVO:01000242.label: desert scrubland
ENVO:01000242.definition: A scrubland which is located in a desert.

ENVO:00000485.label: sea shore
ENVO:00000485.definition: That part of the land in immediate contact with a sea, including the intertidal zone.

ENVO:00000395.label: channel of a watercourse
ENVO:00000395.definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

ENVO:00000514.label: crater
ENVO:00000514.definition: A generally circular saucer or bowl-shaped depression caused by volcanic or meteorite explosive action.

ENVO:00000291.label: drainage basin
ENVO:00000291.definition: An extent or area of land where surface water from rain and melting snow or ice converges to a single point at lower elevation, usually the exit of the basin, where the waters join another waterbody.

ENVO:00000311.label: kettle
ENVO:00000311.definition: A fluvioglacial landform occurring as the result of blocks of ice calving from the front of a receding glacier and becoming partially to wholly buried by glacial outwash. Glacial outwash is generated when sediment laden streams of meltwater flow away from the glacier and are deposited to form broad outwash plains called sandurs. When the ice blocks melt, holes are left in the sandur.

ENVO:03000015.label: geographic basin
ENVO:03000015.definition: A depression which is part of a planetary crust, is of geographic scale, and is partially or completely enclosed.

ENVO:00000341.label: piece of gravel
ENVO:00000341.definition: A piece of rock that is two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension (about 1/12 of an inch) and no more than 75 millimeters (about 3 inches).

ENVO:00000025.label: reservoir
ENVO:00000025.definition: An artificial body of water, often contained by a dam, constructed for the purpose of water storage.

ENVO:00000446.label: terrestrial biome
ENVO:00000446.definition: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

ENVO:01000219.label: anthropogenic terrestrial biome
ENVO:01000219.definition: An anthropogenic terrestrial biome is a terrestrial biome which has community structures determined by human activity.

ENVO:01000179.label: desert biome
ENVO:01000179.definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

ENVO:01000177.label: grassland biome
ENVO:01000177.definition: A grassland biome is a terrestrial biome which  includes, across its entire spatial extent, an unbroken layer of grasses (Gramineae), sedges (Cyperaceae) or  rushes (Juncaceae).

ENVO:01000181.label: mangrove biome
ENVO:01000181.definition: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae). Mangrove plants are able to withstand high levels of salinity as well as regions of anoxia and frequent tidal inundation. Mangrove biomes often occur near tropical and sub-tropical estuaries and depositional marine coastal environments where fine sediments (often with high organic content) collect in areas protected from high energy wave action.

ENVO:01000176.label: shrubland biome
ENVO:01000176.definition: A shrubland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, dense groups of shrubs.

ENVO:01000180.label: tundra biome
ENVO:01000180.definition: A tundra is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, only low-growing vegetation such as dwarf shrubs, sedges and grasses, mosses, and lichens. Tundra biomes rarely have monthly average temperatures above 10 degrees Celsius and have low evapotranspiration ratios.

ENVO:01000023.label: marine pelagic biome
ENVO:01000023.definition: The marine pelagic biome (pelagic meaning open sea) is that of the marine water column, from the surface to the greatest depths.

ENVO:00000137.label: coastal inlet
ENVO:00000137.definition: An opening of the sea into the land.

ENVO:00000476.label: lake inlet
ENVO:00000476.definition: An opening of a lake into its shore.

ENVO:00000433.label: kame terrace
ENVO:00000433.definition: A terrace associated with a kame.

ENVO:00002016.label: sedimentary rock
ENVO:00002016.definition: A rock formed by deposition of either clastic sediments, organic matter, or chemical precipitates (evaporites), followed by compaction of the particulate matter and cementation during diagenesis.

ENVO:00002015.label: volcanic rock
ENVO:00002015.definition: An igneous rock that results from magma reaching the surface either as lava or fragmental ejecta.

ENVO:00002232.label: andosol
ENVO:00002232.definition: Andosols are soils that develop in volcanic ejecta or glasses under almost any climate (except under hyperarid climate conditions). However, Andosols may also develop in other silicate-rich materials under acid weathering in humid and perhumid climates.

ENVO:00002229.label: arenosol
ENVO:00002229.definition: Arenosols are sandy soils, including both soils developed in residual sands after in situ weathering of usually quartz-rich sediments or rock, and soils developed in recently deposited sands such as dunes in deserts and beach lands.

ENVO:00002235.label: cambisol
ENVO:00002235.definition: Cambisols combine soils with at least an incipient subsurface soil formation. Transformation of parent material is evident from structure formation and mostly brownish discoloration, increasing clay percentage, and/or carbonate removal.

ENVO:00002237.label: chernozem
ENVO:00002237.definition: Chernozems are soils with a thick black surface layer that is rich in organic matter.

ENVO:00005748.label: dry soil
ENVO:00005748.definition: Soil which has little to no water content and in which minerals and other soluble chemical entities have either bonded or become adsorbed to sold particles due to insufficient water availability.

ENVO:00003082.label: enriched soil
ENVO:00003082.definition: A portion of enriched soil is a portion of soil with elevated levels of some material entity.

ENVO:00005749.label: farm soil
ENVO:00005749.definition: A portion of soil which is part of a cropland or a rangeland biome.

ENVO:00002246.label: ferralsol
ENVO:00002246.definition: Ferralsols represent the classical, deeply weathered, red or yellow soils of the humid tropics. These soils have diffuse horizon boundaries, a clay assemblage dominated by low-activity clays (mainly kaolinite) and a high content of sesquioxides.

ENVO:00002273.label: fluvisol
ENVO:00002273.definition: Fluvisols accommodate genetically young, azonal soils in alluvial deposits.

ENVO:00002261.label: forest soil
ENVO:00002261.definition: A portion of soil which is found in a forested area.

ENVO:00002244.label: gleysol
ENVO:00002244.definition: Gleysols are wetland soils that, unless drained, are saturated with groundwater for long enough periods to develop a characteristic gleyic colour pattern. This pattern is essentially made up of reddish, brownish or yellowish colours at ped surfaces and/or in the upper soil layer or layers, in combination with greyish/bluish colours inside the peds and/or deeper in the soil.

ENVO:00005750.label: grassland soil
ENVO:00005750.definition: A portion of soil which is found in a grassland.

ENVO:00002245.label: gypsisol
ENVO:00002245.definition: Gypsisols are soils with substantial secondary accumulation of gypsum (calcium sulfate). These soils are found in the driest parts of the arid climate zone.

ENVO:00002243.label: histosol
ENVO:00002243.definition: Histosols comprise soils formed in organic material. These vary from soils developed in predominantly moss peat in boreal, arctic and subarctic regions, via moss peat, reeds/ sedge peat (fen) and forest peat in temperate regions to mangrove peat and swamp forest peat in the humid tropics. Histosols are found at all altitudes, but the vast majority occurs in lowlands.

ENVO:00002240.label: kastanozem
ENVO:00002240.definition: Kastanozems are dry grassland soils, among them the zonal soils of the short-grass steppe belt, south of the Eurasian tall-grass steppe belt with Chernozems. Kastanozems have a similar profile to that of Chernozems but the humus-rich surface horizon is thinner and not as dark as that of the Chernozems and they show more prominent accumulation of secondary carbonates.

ENVO:00002248.label: luvisol
ENVO:00002248.definition: Luvisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Luvisols have high-activity clays throughout the argic horizon and a high base saturation at certain depths.

ENVO:00005767.label: manured soil
ENVO:00005767.definition: Soil which has, as a part, a portion of either fresh or processed animal manure.

ENVO:00002247.label: nitisol
