ENVO:00002247.definition: Nitisols are deep, well-drained, red, tropical soils with diffuse horizon boundaries and a subsurface horizon with more than 30 percent clay and moderate to strong angular blocky structure elements that easily fall apart into characteristic shiny, polyhedric (nutty) elements. Weathering is relatively advanced but Nitisols are far more productive than most other red, tropical soils.

ENVO:00002249.label: phaeozem
ENVO:00002249.definition: Phaeozems accommodate soils of relatively wet grassland and forest regions in moderately continental climates. Phaeozems are much like Chernozems and Kastanozems but are leached more intensively. Consequently, they have dark, humus rich surface horizons that, in comparison with Chernozems and Kastanozems, are less rich in bases. Phaeozems may or may not have secondary carbonates but have a high base saturation in the upper metre of the soil.

ENVO:00002257.label: podzol
ENVO:00002257.definition: Podzols are soils with a typically ash-grey upper subsurface horizon, bleached by loss of organic matter and iron oxides, on top of a dark accumulation horizon with brown, reddish or black illuviated humus and/or reddish Fe compounds. Podzols occur in humid areas in the boreal and temperate zones and locally also in the tropics.

ENVO:00002256.label: regosol
ENVO:00002256.definition: Regosols form a taxonomic remnant group containing all soils that could not be accommodated in any of the other RSGs. In practice, Regosols are very weakly developed mineral soils in unconsolidated materials that do not have a mollic or umbric horizon, are not very shallow or very rich in gravels (Leptosols), sandy (Arenosols) or with fluvic materials (Fluvisols). Regosols are extensive in eroding lands, particularly in arid and semi-arid areas and in mountainous terrain.

ENVO:00002252.label: solonchak
ENVO:00002252.definition: Solonchaks are soils that have a high concentration of soluble salts at some time in the year. Solonchaks are largely confined to the arid and semi-arid climate zones and to coastal regions in all climates.

ENVO:00002255.label: solonetz
ENVO:00002255.definition: Solonetz are soils with a dense, strongly structured, clayey subsurface horizon that has a high proportion of adsorbed Na and/or Mg ions. Solonetz that contain free soda (Na2CO3) are strongly alkaline (field pH > 8.5).

ENVO:00002254.label: vertisol
ENVO:00002254.definition: A soil in which there is a high content of expansive clay known as montmorillonite that forms deep cracks in drier seasons or years. Alternate shrinking and swelling causes self-mulching, where the soil material consistently mixes itself, causing vertisols to have an extremely deep A horizon and no B horizon.

ENVO:01001526.label: frozen soil
ENVO:01001526.definition: Soil which is below the freezing point of water.

ENVO:01001397.label: ultisol
ENVO:01001397.definition: A soil which has high mineral content and which contain no calcareous material, have less than 10% weatherable minerals its surface layer, and have less than 35% base saturation throughout its volume.

ENVO:02000049.label: coastal water body
ENVO:02000049.definition: Coastal water is a marine water body bordering a coast.

ENVO:00000015.label: ocean
ENVO:00000015.definition: A marine water body which is constitutes the majority of an astronomical body's hydrosphere.

ENVO:00000016.label: sea
ENVO:00000016.definition: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.

ENVO:00000141.label: bank
ENVO:00000141.definition: The sloping margin of a watercourse, serving to confine it to its natural channel.

ENVO:00000280.label: escarpment
ENVO:00000280.definition: A slope which separates different physiogeographic provinces that are typically composed of rocks of different age and compositoin.

ENVO:01000332.label: gravelly slope
ENVO:01000332.definition: A gravelly slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of gravel.

ENVO:01000333.label: hillside
ENVO:01000333.definition: A hillside is a slope that is part of a hill.

ENVO:01000319.label: rocky slope
ENVO:01000319.definition: A rocky slope is a slope which has a surface primarily composed of rock.

ENVO:01000334.label: talus slope
ENVO:01000334.definition: A talus slope is a slope which has a surface layer composed of scree.

ENVO:00002011.label: fresh water
ENVO:00002011.definition: Water which has a low concentration of dissolved solutes, particularly that of sodium chloride.

ENVO:00002010.label: saline water
ENVO:00002010.definition: Water which contains a significant concentration of dissolved salts.

ENVO:00002042.label: surface water
ENVO:00002042.definition: Water that is found on the surface of an astronomical object.

ENVO:00002045.label: anaerobic sediment
ENVO:00002045.definition: Sediment characterised by the absence of oxygen.

ENVO:03000033.label: marine sediment
ENVO:03000033.definition: Sediment which has been transported through the marine water column, settling on the seafloor.

ENVO:02000105.label: clay dust
ENVO:02000105.definition: Dust which is derived from clay material.

ENVO:02000103.label: metallic dust
ENVO:02000103.definition: Dust which is composed primarily of some metallic material.

ENVO:02000100.label: mineral dust
ENVO:02000100.definition: Dust which is derived from mineral material.

ENVO:00002149.label: sea water
ENVO:00002149.definition: Water which has physicochemical properties that have been determined by the processes occuring in a sea or ocean.

ENVO:00000447.label: marine biome
ENVO:00000447.definition: An aquatic biome that comprises systems of open-ocean and unprotected coastal habitats, characterized by exposure to wave action, tidal fluctuation, and ocean currents as well as systems that largely resemble these. Water in the marine biome is generally within the salinity range of seawater: 30 to 38 ppt.

AGRO:00002044.label: calcitic limestone
AGRO:00002044.definition: A limestone that is derived from deposits of primarily calcium carbonate.

AGRO:00002045.label: dolomitic limestone
AGRO:00002045.definition: A limestone that is derived from deposits of calcium carbonate combined with magnesium carbonate and contains high levels of magnesium.

ENVO:00002150.label: coastal sea water
ENVO:00002150.definition: Coastal sea water is sea water that is adjacent to a coast.

AGRO:00000091.label: spent mushroom compost
AGRO:00000091.definition: A compost that contains the residual compost waste generated by mushroom production. It  generally consists of a combination of wheat straw, dried blood, horse manure and ground chalk, composted together.

AGRO:00002042.label: vermicompost
AGRO:00002042.definition: A compost that is the product of the decomposition process using various species of worms, usually red wigglers, white worms, and other earthworms, to create a mixture of decomposing vegetable or food waste, bedding materials, and vermicast.

ENVO:00000131.label: glacial feature
ENVO:00000131.definition: A hydrographic feature characterized by the dominance of snow or ice.

ENVO:01000637.label: outer space
ENVO:01000637.definition: Outer space is a hard vacuum containing a low density of particles, predominantly a plasma of hydrogen and helium as well as electromagnetic radiation, magnetic fields, neutrinos, dust and cosmic rays that exists between celestial bodies.

ENVO:01001120.label: animal manure product
ENVO:01001120.definition: A product which is composed primarily of animal manure that has been heat treated and packaged as a product for commercial or consumer use.

ENVO:00003074.label: manufactured product
ENVO:00003074.definition: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.

ENVO:00005773.label: pasture soil
ENVO:00005773.definition: Soil which is found in a pasture and in which vegetation, such as the grass used for the grazing of ungulates, grows.

ENVO:00005746.label: savanna soil
ENVO:00005746.definition: A portion of soil which is found in a savanna.

ENVO:00005777.label: steppe soil
ENVO:00005777.definition: A portion of soil which is found in a steppe.

ENVO:00010505.label: aerosol
ENVO:00010505.definition: Airborne solid particles (also called dust or particulate matter (PM)) or liquid droplets.

ENVO:0010001.label: anthropogenic environmental material
ENVO:0010001.definition: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

ENVO:00002982.label: clay
ENVO:00002982.definition: A group of hydrous aluminium phyllosilicate (phyllosilicates being a subgroup of silicate minerals) minerals (see clay minerals), that are typically less than 2 micrometres in diameter. Clay consists of a variety of phyllosilicate minerals rich in silicon and aluminium oxides and hydroxides which include variable amounts of structural water.

ENVO:01000018.label: gravel
ENVO:01000018.definition: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.

ENVO:01000155.label: organic material
ENVO:01000155.definition: Environmental material derived from living organisms and composed primarily of one or more biomacromolecules.

ENVO:00000134.label: permafrost
ENVO:00000134.definition: Soil or rock and included ice or organic material at or below the freezing point of water (0 degrees Celsius or 32 degrees Fahrenheit) for two or more years.

ENVO:01000017.label: sand
ENVO:01000017.definition: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.

ENVO:00000194.label: scree
ENVO:00000194.definition: Broken rock that appears at the bottom of crags, mountain cliffs or valley shoulders.

ENVO:00002007.label: sediment
ENVO:00002007.definition: Sediment is an environmental substance comprised of any particulate matter that can be transported by fluid flow and which eventually is deposited as a layer of solid particles on the bedor bottom of a body of water or other liquid.

ENVO:01000016.label: silt
ENVO:01000016.definition: Silt is granular material of a size somewhere between sand and clay whose mineral origin is quartz and feldspar.

ENVO:01000406.label: snow
ENVO:01000406.definition: Snow is an environmental material which is primarily composed of flakes of crystalline water ice.

ENVO:00001998.label: soil
ENVO:00001998.definition: Soil is an environmental material which is primarily composed of minerals, varying proportions of sand, silt, and clay, organic material such as humus, gases, liquids, and a broad range of resident micro- and macroorganisms.

ENVO:00002264.label: waste material
ENVO:00002264.definition: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.g. a disposal process).

AGRO:00002062.label: agronomic fertilizer
AGRO:00002062.definition: An enviromental material that has a role of fertilization

ENVO:01000797.label: gaseous environmental material
ENVO:01000797.definition: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.

ENVO:01001125.label: ice
ENVO:01001125.definition: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

AGRO:00000197.label: liming material
AGRO:00000197.definition: An environmental material containing calcium and/or magnesium compounds  and applied to soil in order to neutralize soil acidity.

ENVO:01000815.label: liquid environmental material
ENVO:01000815.definition: An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

ENVO:01000648.label: magma
ENVO:01000648.definition: Magma is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids that is found beneath the uppermost solid layer of a planetary body. Besides molten rock, magma may also contain suspended crystals, dissolved gas and sometimes gas bubbles.

ENVO:01000853.label: marl
ENVO:01000853.definition: Marl is a mass of calcium carbonate derived from mollusk shells and mixed with silt and clay.

ENVO:01001069.label: metallic material
ENVO:01001069.definition: A material which is composed primarily of one or more pure metals and which shows their properties.

AGRO:00000092.label: mulch
AGRO:00000092.definition: Layer of material applied to the soil surface to conserve moisture, improve soil fertility, reduce weed growth, or enhance the visual appeal of the area.

ENVO:01000060.label: particulate matter
ENVO:01000060.definition: Particulate material is an environmental material which is composed of microscopic portions of solid or liquid material suspended in another environmental material.

ENVO:01001154.label: volatile astrogeological material
ENVO:01001154.definition: A material which is composed primarily of chemical elements and compounds with relatively low boiling points, equilibrium condensation temperatures below 1300 Kelvin, and which are part of the crust or atmosphere of a moon or planet.

ENVO:01000324.label: planetary surface
ENVO:01000324.definition: A planetary surface is a surface layer where the solid or liquid material of a planet comes into contact with an atmosphere or outer space.

ENVO:01001310.label: liquid surface layer
ENVO:01001310.definition: A liquid surface layer which is in contact with air.

ENVO:01001192.label: sediment surface
ENVO:01001192.definition: The surface layer of a mass of sediment.

ENVO:01001311.label: solid surface layer
ENVO:01001311.definition: A surface layer which is composed primarily of solid environmental material.

ENVO:01001088.label: aerosolised liquids
ENVO:01001088.definition: An aerosol which has non-gaseous parts that are primarily composed of liquid droplets.

ENVO:01001089.label: aerosolised solids
ENVO:01001089.definition: An aerosol which has non-gaseous parts that are primarily composed of solid particles.

ENVO:00002869.label: hay
ENVO:00002869.definition: Hay is grass, legumes or other herbaceous plants that have been cut, dried, and stored for use as animal fodder, particularly for grazing livestock such as cattle, horses, goats, and sheep.

ENVO:00003030.label: silage
ENVO:00003030.definition: A fermented, high-moisture forage that can be fed to ruminants.

ENVO:00003869.label: straw
ENVO:00003869.definition: An agricultural byproduct, the dry stalk of a cereal plant, after the nutrient grain or seed has been removed.

ENVO:02000055.label: plant feed
ENVO:02000055.definition: Plant feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed plants.

ENVO:00000339.label: piece of rock
ENVO:00000339.definition: An abiotic  mesoscopic feature made of the mineral material of the crust of the Earth.

ENVO:01000032.label: neritic pelagic zone biome
ENVO:01000032.definition: The neritic epipelagic zone biome comprises the marine water column above a continental shelf.

ENVO:01000033.label: oceanic pelagic zone biome
ENVO:01000033.definition: The oceanic epipelagic zone biome comprises the marine water column offshore, beyond a continental shelf.

ENVO:01000041.label: neritic sea surface microlayer biome
ENVO:01000041.definition: The neritic sea surface microlayer (SML) biome comprises the top 1000 micrometers of marine surface waters occurring above a continental shelf. It is the boundary layer where all exchange occurs between the atmosphere and the ocean. The chemical, physical, and biological properties of the SML differ greatly from the sub-surface water just a few centimeters beneath.

ENVO:01000034.label: oceanic sea surface microlayer biome
ENVO:01000034.definition: The oceanic sea surface microlayer (SML) biome comprises the top 1000 micrometers of the marine surface waters occurring offshore, away from a continental shelf. It is the boundary layer where all exchange occurs between the atmosphere and the ocean. The chemical, physical, and biological properties of the SML differ greatly from the sub-surface water just a few centimeters beneath.

ENVO:01000295.label: marine layer
ENVO:01000295.definition: A layer that is part of a marine water body.

ENVO:00001999.label: marine water body
ENVO:00001999.definition: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

ENVO:00002008.label: dust
ENVO:00002008.definition: Minute solid particles with diameters less than 500 micrometers. Occurs in and may be deposited from, the atmosphere.

ENVO:01000216.label: montane shrubland biome
ENVO:01000216.definition: A montane shrubland biome is a shrubland biome which occurs in regions elevated above sea level and which has community structure determined by elevation-dependent environmental conditions.

ENVO:01000343.label: altitudinal condition
ENVO:01000343.definition: An altitudinal condition is an environmental condition in which ranges of factors such as temperature, humidity, soil composition, solar irradiation, and tree density vary with ranges in altitude.

ENVO:01000230.label: arid
ENVO:01000230.definition: An environmental condition in which annual precipitation is less than half of annual potential evapotranspiration.

ENVO:01000205.label: subtropical
ENVO:01000205.definition: A subtropical condition is an environmental condition in which an envrionmental system receives more solar irradiance than those with temperate conditions, but less than those with tropical conditions. At low elevations, this typically results in eight months of the year having average temperatures greater than or equal to 10 degrees Celsius with the coldest monthly temperature averaging between 2 and 13 degrees Celsius.

ENVO:01000204.label: tropical
ENVO:01000204.definition: A tropical condition is an environmental condition in which an environmental system receives high yearly solar irradiance per unit area and, on Earth, the Sun reaches a subsolar point at least once during the solar year. This results in a hot and moist year-round climate at low elevations, which have a monthly average temperature above 18 degrees Celsius.

ENVO:01000375.label: tropical marine condition
ENVO:01000375.definition: A tropical marine condition is a tropical condition in which the ocean strongly influences the climate and a wet and dry season occur.

ENVO:01000245.label: cropland biome
ENVO:01000245.definition: A cropland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for agricultural activity and which contains no village or larger human settlement.

ENVO:01000248.label: dense settlement biome
ENVO:01000248.definition: A dense settlement biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for human habitation, recreation, and industry within built structures with little other land use.

ENVO:01000247.label: rangeland biome
ENVO:01000247.definition: A rangeland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for the rearing and grazing of livestock.

ENVO:2100000.label: anatomical entity environment
ENVO:2100000.definition: An environment which is determined by an anatomical entity.

ENVO:01000313.label: anthropogenic environment
ENVO:01000313.definition: An anthropogenic environment is an environmental system which is the product of human activity.

ENVO:01000309.label: cold environment
ENVO:01000309.definition: An environment which has a lower temperature than some local or global average.

ENVO:01000303.label: endolithic environment
ENVO:01000303.definition: An endolithic environment is an environment that exists within solid rock.

ENVO:01000320.label: marine environment
ENVO:01000320.definition: A marine environment and enviroment which is determined by a marine water body.

ENVO:01001110.label: ecosystem
ENVO:01001110.definition: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.

ENVO:01000998.label: environmental system determined by a material
ENVO:01000998.definition: An environmental system within which an environmental material strongly influences the system's composition and properties.

ENVO:01000997.label: environmental system determined by a quality
ENVO:01000997.definition: An environmental system which is determined by materials bearing roughly homogeneous qualities.

ENVO:01000951.label: natural environment
ENVO:01000951.definition: An environmental system in which minimal to no anthropisation has occurred and non-human agents are the primary determinants of the system's dynamics and composition.

ENVO:01000268.label: atmospheric water vapour
ENVO:01000268.definition: Atmospheric water vapour is water vapour that is part of an atmosphere.

ENVO:01001570.label: terrestrial ecoregion
ENVO:01001570.definition: An ecoregion which is located on a landmass.

ENVO:01000267.label: atmosphere
ENVO:01000267.definition: An atmosphere is a layer of gases surrounding a material body of sufficient mass that is held in place by the gravity of the body.

ENVO:00010504.label: surface layer
ENVO:00010504.definition: A layer of some material entity which is adjacent to one or more of its external boundaries and directly interacts with its immediate surroundings.

ENVO:01000355.label: vegetation layer
ENVO:01000355.definition: A layer which is determined by a form of vegetation.

ENVO:01000544.label: boundary layer
ENVO:01000544.definition: A boundary layer is a layer of fluid in the immediate vicinity of a bounding surface where the effects of viscosity are significant enough to distort the surrounding non-viscous flow.

ENVO:01001273.label: liquid layer
ENVO:01001273.definition: A layer which is primarily composed of some liquid material.

ENVO:01000639.label: planetary structural layer
ENVO:01000639.definition: A planetary structural layer is laminar part of a terrestrial planet or other rocky body large enough to have differentiation by density. Planetary layers have differing physicochemical properties and composition.

ENVO:01001483.label: surface of an astronomical body
ENVO:01001483.definition: A surface layer where the solid or liquid material of an astronomical body comes into contact with an atmosphere or outer space.

ENVO:01001581.label: sea surface layer
ENVO:01001581.definition: A surface layer of a water body which is part of an ocean or sea.

ENVO:01000321.label: sea water environment
ENVO:01000321.definition: An environmental system determined by seawater.

ENVO:01001040.label: saline environment
ENVO:01001040.definition: An environment which is determined by materials which bear significant concentrations of salts.

ENVO:01000306.label: freshwater environment
ENVO:01000306.definition: An aquatic environment which is determined by freshwater.

ENVO:01000307.label: saline water environment
ENVO:01000307.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by saline water.

ENVO:01000635.label: land
ENVO:01000635.definition: Land is a planetary surface that is not covered by liquid.

ENVO:01000283.label: lake layer
ENVO:01000283.definition: A layer which is part of a lake.

ENVO:01001191.label: water surface
ENVO:01001191.definition: The surface layer of a volume of water.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: surface of a body of water
surface of a body of water

ENVO:01000342.label: montane
ENVO:01000342.definition: A montane condition is an environmental condition in which an altitude range falls between mid-altitude forests and the tree line.

ENVO:00000114.label: agricultural field
ENVO:00000114.definition: A field which is located on land and used for agricultural purposes, such as the grazing of livestock or the cultivation of crops.

ENVO:01001242.label: canopy
ENVO:01001242.definition: A vegetation layer which is formed by a collection of individual plant crowns, themselves constituting part of the aboveground portion of a plant community.

ENVO:01000276.label: ecoregion
ENVO:01000276.definition: A large unit of land or water containing a geographically distinct assemblage of species, natural communities, and environmental conditions.

ENVO:01000280.label: ecozone
ENVO:01000280.definition: Ecozones delineate large areas of a planetary surface within which organisms have been evolving in relative isolation over long periods of time, separated from one another by geographic features, such as oceans, broad deserts, or high mountain ranges, that constitute barriers to migration.

AGRO:00000301.label: agricultural experimental plot
AGRO:00000301.definition: A site within which an agricultural experimental process is conducted

ENVO:01001299.label: atmospheric zone
ENVO:01001299.definition: An environmental zone which is part of an atmosphere.

AGRO:00000303.label: block
AGRO:00000303.definition: A block is a relatively large area or several identical units receiving all or most of the treatments. A collection of plots is called a block.

AGRO:00000196.label: bund
AGRO:00000196.definition: Small earth embankment which contain irrigation water within basins.

ENVO:01000687.label: coast
ENVO:01000687.definition: A coast is the area where land meets the sea, ocean, or lake.

AGRO:00000420.label: column
AGRO:00000420.definition: Vertical arrangement of plants in a field.

AGRO:00000360.label: experimental site
AGRO:00000360.definition: Location where the experiment is implemented.

AGRO:00000156.label: interrow
AGRO:00000156.definition: A site which is located between two rows of crop plants.

ENVO:01001201.label: marine environmental zone
ENVO:01001201.definition: An environmental zone which is bounded by material parts of a marine environment.

AGRO:00000309.label: pot
AGRO:00000309.definition: A rounded container used to cultivate plant.

AGRO:00000155.label: row
AGRO:00000155.definition: two or more crop plants planted in a line.

AGRO:00002017.label: seedbed
AGRO:00002017.definition: An environmental zone prepared for growing plants.

ENVO:01001098.label: tectonic plate boundary
ENVO:01001098.definition: A geomorphological feature which is formed where two or more tectonic plates move towards, away from, or along one another, resulting in deformation of the lithosphere.

ENVO:01001199.label: terrestrial environmental zone
ENVO:01001199.definition: An environmental zone which is bounded by material parts of a land mass or the atmosphere or space adjacent to it.

ENVO:01000481.label: silica-based glass
ENVO:01000481.definition: Silica-based glass is a glass composed primarily of silicon dioxide, the primary constituent of sand.

ENVO:01000323.label: atmospheric boundary layer
ENVO:01000323.definition: The atmospheric boundary layer is the lowest layer of an atmosphere which is strongly influenced by its contact with a planetary surface with strong vertical mixing and in which physical quantities such as flow velocity, temperature, and moisture display rapid fluctuations (turbulence).

AGRO:00020002.label: biochar
AGRO:00020002.definition: charcoal used as a soil amendment.

ENVO:01001524.label: frozen land
ENVO:01001524.definition: Land which is below the freezing point of water.

ENVO:01000646.label: lithosphere
ENVO:01000646.definition: A lithosphere is the outermost shell of a terrestrial-type planet or natural satellite that is defined by its rigid mechanical properties.

ENVO:01000638.label: planetary crust
ENVO:01000638.definition: A planetary crust is the outermost solid shell of a rocky planet or natural satellite, which is chemically distinct from the underlying mantle.

ENVO:01000640.label: planetary mantle
ENVO:01000640.definition: A planetary mantle is a planetary layer which is an interior part of a terrestrial planet or other rocky body large enough to have differentiation by density.

ENVO:00000063.label: water body
ENVO:00000063.definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.

ENVO:00000303.label: sea coast
ENVO:00000303.definition: The general region of indefinite width that extends from the sea inland to the first major change in terrain features.

ENVO:1000745.label: drought
ENVO:1000745.definition: A hydrological precipitation process with a reduced rate relative to some historical average, typically resulting in ecosystemic perturbations.

ENVO:01000895.label: snowfall
ENVO:01000895.definition: A hydrological process in which irregular aggregates of snow fall to a planetary surface.

ENVO:01000624.label: hydrological condensation process
ENVO:01000624.definition: Hydrological condensation is a process in which atmospheric water vapour undergoes a phase transition from the gas phase to the liquid phase.

ENVO:00000097.label: desert area
ENVO:00000097.definition: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

ENVO:01000788.label: conflagration
ENVO:01000788.definition: A fire which occurs in a large spatial area poses a risk to human life, animal life, health, and/or property.

ENVO:01000787.label: wildfire
ENVO:01000787.definition: A conflagration which is uncontrolled and combusts material in a vegetated area, be it rural or wild.

ENVO:01000790.label: hydrocarbon flame
ENVO:01000790.definition: A flame which is produced by the combustion of hydrocarbon fuel.

ENVO:00002005.label: air
ENVO:00002005.definition: The mixture of gases (roughly (by molar content/volume: 78% nitrogen, 20.95% oxygen, 0.93% argon, 0.038% carbon dioxide, trace amounts of other gases, and a variable amount (average around 1%) of water vapor) that surrounds the planet Earth.

ENVO:01000266.label: water vapour
ENVO:01000266.definition: Water vapour is a vapour which is the gas phase of water.

ENVO:01000789.label: flame
ENVO:01000789.definition: A portion of gas which is emitted by a fire or other exothermic reaction, is of increased temperature, and typically emits light in the visible range.

ENVO:01000554.label: hydrocarbon gas
ENVO:01000554.definition: A gas that is primarily composed of hydrocarbon molecules.

ENVO:01001068.label: meteoroid
ENVO:01001068.definition: An astronomical body which is composed of rocky or metallic materials and is considerably smaller than asteroids.

ENVO:01000800.label: planet
ENVO:01000800.definition: A planet is an astronomical body orbiting a star or stellar remnant that is massive enough to be rounded by its own gravity, is not massive enough to cause thermonuclear fusion, and has cleared its neighbouring region of planetesimals.

ENVO:01001122.label: gas planet
ENVO:01001122.definition: A planet which is primarily composed of hydrogen and helium.

ENVO:01001137.label: ice planet
ENVO:01001137.definition: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by ice, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of ice.

ENVO:01001136.label: ocean planet
ENVO:01001136.definition: A planet which has a surface layer that nearly completely or completely covered by water, and which has a substantial portion of its mass composed of water.

ENVO:01000958.label: terrestrial planet
ENVO:01000958.definition: A planet that is composed primarily of silicate rocks or metals.

ENVO:01000799.label: astronomical body
ENVO:01000799.definition: An object which is naturally occuring, bound together by gravitational or electromagnetic forces, and surrounded by space.

ENVO:00000191.label: solid astronomical body part
ENVO:00000191.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of solid material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:00000094.label: volcanic feature
ENVO:00000094.definition: A part of an astronomical body associated with a volcano - an opening, or rupture, in that body's surface or crust - which allows hot, molten rock, ash and gases to escape from deep below the surface.

ENVO:01000817.label: biosphere
ENVO:01000817.definition: A biosphere is an environmental system which includes, as parts, all the living entities within the gravitational sphere of influence of an astronomical body, and the non-living and dead entities which they interact with.

ENVO:01001479.label: fluid astronomical body part
ENVO:01001479.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid or gaseous material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:01000983.label: technosphere
ENVO:01000983.definition: A part of an astronomical body which includes, as parts, all the entities which have been constructed or manufactured by humans or their technology and which are within the gravitational sphere of influence of that body.

ENVO:01000480.label: glass
ENVO:01000480.definition: Glass is an amorphous (non-crystalline) solid which is often transparent.

ENVO:01000256.label: mineral material
ENVO:01000256.definition: A mineral material is an environmental material which is primarily composed of some substance that is naturally occurring, solid and stable at room temperature, representable by a chemical formula, usually abiogenic, and that has an ordered atomic structure.

ENVO:00001995.label: rock
ENVO:00001995.definition: A rock is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals or mineraloids.

ENVO:01000277.label: water ice
ENVO:01000277.definition: Ice is water frozen into a solid state. It can appear transparent or opaque bluish-white color, depending on the presence of impurities or air inclusions. The addition of other materials such as soil may further alter its appearance.

ENVO:00002006.label: liquid water
ENVO:00002006.definition: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

ENVO:01000786.label: fire
ENVO:01000786.definition: A fire is a process whereby rapid and exothermic oxidation of a material through a combustion process releases heat, light, and other products.

ENVO:01000839.label: combustion process
ENVO:01000839.definition: Combustion or burning is a high-temperature exothermic redox chemical reaction between a fuel and an oxidant that produces oxidized, often gaseous products, in a mixture termed as smoke.

ENVO:01000841.label: pyrolysis
ENVO:01000841.definition: A thermolysis process in which organic material is decomposed in the absence of oxygen.

ENVO:01000703.label: hydrological precipitation process
ENVO:01000703.definition: Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.

ENVO:01000953.label: tree line ecotone
ENVO:01000953.definition: An ecotone which overlaps at least one biome which supports the growth and persistence of trees and at least one that does not. Before ceasing altogether, tree growth becomes sparse and trees appear stunted as conditions become less favourable along this ecotone.

ENVO:01001227.label: aquatic natural environment
ENVO:01001227.definition: A natural environment which is within a water body.

ENVO:01001226.label: terrestrial natural environment
ENVO:01001226.definition: A natural environment which is located on a land mass.

ENVO:01000996.label: construction process
ENVO:01000996.definition: An process during which natural or manufactured materials and products are processed and arranged by humans or their technology into structures.

ENVO:01000993.label: manufacturing process
ENVO:01000993.definition: A planned process during which raw or recycled materials are transformed into products for use or sale using labour and machines, tools, chemical and biological processing, or formulation.

ENVO:01001135.label: desert planet
ENVO:01001135.definition: A terrestrial planet which has a surface dominated by hot deserts.

ENVO:01000982.label: water flow process
ENVO:01000982.definition: A process during which a volume of water is transported due to a disequilibria in physical forces.

ENVO:01000317.label: aquatic environment
ENVO:01000317.definition: An environment whose dynamics are strongly influenced by water.

ENVO:01000314.label: high osmolarity environment
ENVO:01000314.definition: A high osmolarity environment is an environment in which entities are exposed to high concentrations of solutes.

ENVO:01000305.label: high temperature environment
ENVO:01000305.definition: A high temperature environment is an environment in which material entities are exposed to increased levels of heat radiation or which have molecules or atoms moving randomly with increased levels of average kinietic energy.

ENVO:01001052.label: aerosol environment
ENVO:01001052.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol.

ENVO:01001048.label: sediment environment
ENVO:01001048.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by sediment.

ENVO:01001044.label: soil environment
ENVO:01001044.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by soil.

ENVO:01001002.label: animal-associated environment
ENVO:01001002.definition: An environmental system determined by an animal.

ENVO:01001001.label: plant-associated environment
ENVO:01001001.definition: An environmental system determined by a green plant.

ENVO:01001176.label: environment associated with an aquatic invertebrate
ENVO:01001176.definition: An environment which has its properties and composition largely determined by the presence of a metazoan which lacks a vetebral column and which has a habitat that is found in an aquatic environmental system.

ENVO:01001010.label: hydrometeor
ENVO:01001010.definition: A meteor which is primarily composed of water.

ENVO:01001012.label: lithometeor
ENVO:01001012.definition: A meteor which is primarily composed of rock.

ENVO:01001053.label: saline aerosol environment
ENVO:01001053.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by a saline aerosol.

ENVO:01001054.label: non-saline aerosol environment
ENVO:01001054.definition: An environmental system which has its properties and dynamics determined by an aerosol with a low concentration of dissolved solutes.

ENVO:00000428.label: biome
ENVO:00000428.definition: A biome is an ecosystem to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

ENVO:01001244.label: cropland ecosystem
ENVO:01001244.definition: An ecosystem which is determined by communities of annual crops, perennial woody crops, or by actively tilled land.

ENVO:01000947.label: ecotone
ENVO:01000947.definition: An envirommental system which bridges two or more biomes and which includes ecological communities which blend these biomes' phylogenetic and phenotypic compositions.

ENVO:01001057.label: environment associated with a plant part or small plant
ENVO:01001057.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead plant, or a whole small plant.

ENVO:01001055.label: environment associated with an animal part or small animal
ENVO:01001055.definition: An environmental system determined by part of a living or dead animal, or a whole small animal.

ENVO:01001000.label: environmental system determined by an organism
ENVO:01001000.definition: An environmental system which is determined by a living organism.

ENVO:01001243.label: forest ecosystem
ENVO:01001243.definition: An ecosystem which is determined by communities of plants with a tree growth form and in which members of those communities form continuous or discontinuous regions of canopy cover.

ENVO:01001206.label: grassland ecosystem
ENVO:01001206.definition: An ecosystem in which grasses (Graminae) are the dominant form of vegetation and determine the system's structure and dynamics.

ENVO:01000739.label: habitat
ENVO:01000739.definition: An environmental system which can sustain and allow the growth of an ecological population.

ENVO:01001370.label: tundra ecosystem
ENVO:01001370.definition: An ecosystem which 1) typically has monthly average temperatures below 10 degrees Celsius 2) has a low evapotranspiration ratio and 3) is determined by communities of low-growing vegetation such as dwarf shrubs, sedges and grasses, mosses, and lichens.

ENVO:01001209.label: wetland ecosystem
ENVO:01001209.definition: A terrestrial ecosystem which is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances does support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.

ENVO:01001147.label: helium planet
ENVO:01001147.definition: A gas planet which has an atmosphere composed primarily of helium.

ENVO:01000814.label: solid environmental material
ENVO:01000814.definition: An environmental material which is in a solid state.

ENVO:01001155.label: astrogeological gas
ENVO:01001155.definition: An astrogeological volatile which is composed primarily of chemical compounds with boiling points around those of hydrogen and helium.

ENVO:01001554.label: surface layer of a water body
ENVO:01001554.definition: A water surface that is part of a water body.

ENVO:01001305.label: vegetated area
ENVO:01001305.definition: A vegetated area is a geographic feature which has ground cover dominated by plant communities.

ENVO:01001200.label: anthropised terrestrial environmental zone
ENVO:01001200.definition: A terrestrial zone which is bounded by constructed, manufactured, or other anthropogenic material entities.

ENVO:01000752.label: area of barren land
ENVO:01000752.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily composed of bedrock, desert pavement, scarp rock, talus, material exposed by slides, volcanic material, glacial debris, sand, material exposed during strip mining, gravel, and other accumulations of earthen material in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:00000078.label: farm
ENVO:00000078.definition: An area of land which is used for the cultivation of crops or grazing of livestock, including any agricultural constructions therein.

ENVO:01000883.label: area of developed open space
ENVO:01000883.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by cultivated or anthropically maintained vegetation planted for recreation, erosion control, or aesthetic purposes interspersed by constructed or manufactured objects and materials. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:01000772.label: rural area
ENVO:01000772.definition: An area which is outside of a town, city, or urban area. Rural areas are primarily used for agriculture or pastoralism and may contain rural settlements.

ENVO:00000108.label: meadow ecosystem
ENVO:00000108.definition: A grassland ecosystem which contains a variety of annual, biennial and perennial plants growing on rolling or flat terrain.

ENVO:00000230.label: coastal wetland ecosystem
ENVO:00000230.definition: A wetland ecosystem which overlaps both terrestrial and marine ecosystems.

ENVO:00000243.label: freshwater wetland ecosystem
ENVO:00000243.definition: A wetland which is inundated with water that contains low concentrations of salts.

ENVO:00000233.label: swamp ecosystem
ENVO:00000233.definition: A wetland ecosystem in which land mass is permanently inundated by shallow bodies of water, generally with a substantial number of hummocks, or dry-land protrusions.

ENVO:00000119.label: planted forest
ENVO:00000119.definition: A forest that has been intentionally established by human intervention.

ENVO:01000376.label: tropical marine semi-evergreen forest
ENVO:01000376.definition: A semi-evergreen forest is a forest which undergoes a long dry season and, as a consequence, has a two-storey layer structure,  a dry canopy, a leaf litter layer that only decays during moist periods trees with very small leaves or which shed their leaves to conserve water and which flower during the dry season and grow during the wet season.

ENVO:01000768.label: primary forest
ENVO:01000768.definition: Forest which originally covered a region before changes in the environment brought about by people. (Source: PHC)

ENVO:01000325.label: aquatic layer
ENVO:01000325.definition: A layer in a water mass, itself composed primarily of water.

ENVO:01000869.label: area of scrub
ENVO:01000869.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by a shrubs, young trees, or stunted trees.. The surfaces of this area are in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:00000156.label: desert oasis
ENVO:00000156.definition: A small, isolated, fertile or green area in a desert region, usually having a spring or well.

ENVO:00000106.label: grassland area
ENVO:00000106.definition: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.

ENVO:01001304.label: oasis
ENVO:01001304.definition: An oasis is a vegetated area located in a desert, supplied with water from a water source which it surrounds, and surrounded by arid soil, sand, or rock.

ENVO:00000300.label: scrubland area
ENVO:00000300.definition: Area covered with low-growing or stunted perennial vegetation and usually not mixed with trees.

ENVO:00000112.label: tundra
ENVO:00000112.definition: A vegetated area which overlaps treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, permanently frozen subsoil, and communities of low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.

ENVO:00000043.label: wetland area
ENVO:00000043.definition: An vegetated area which overlaps a wetland ecosystem.

ENVO:00000109.label: woodland area
ENVO:00000109.definition: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.

ENVO:01000887.label: area of sedge- and forb-dominated herbaceous vegetation
ENVO:01000887.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily covered by sedges or forbs, possibly interpersed with grasses or grass-like plants. This area is in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:01001293.label: bush area
ENVO:01001293.definition: A vegetated area which has not been cleared or is sparsely settled, usually scrub-covered or forested

ENVO:01000848.label: flower strip
ENVO:01000848.definition: A vegetated area which includes a community of flowering plants that provide food for local pollinators.

ENVO:01001309.label: liquid air-water interface layer
ENVO:01001309.definition: A liquid surface layer which is in contact with air.

ENVO:01000792.label: mass gaseous flow
ENVO:01000792.definition: A process whereby a large volume of gas moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.

ENVO:01000981.label: mass liquid flow
ENVO:01000981.definition: A process whereby a volume of liquid moves due to a disequilibrium of physical forces.

ENVO:02500028.label: planetary erosion
ENVO:02500028.definition: An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove environmental material from one part of a planet's crust, transporting it to another location where it is deposited.

ENVO:00002234.label: acrisol
ENVO:00002234.definition: Acrisols are soils that have a higher clay content in the subsoil than in the topsoil as a result of pedogenetic processes (especially clay migration) leading to an argic subsoil horizon. Acrisols have in certain depths a low base saturation and low-activity clays.

ENVO:01000952.label: anthropisation
ENVO:01000952.definition: A process during which a natural environmental system is altered by human action.

ENVO:01001308.label: hydroform
ENVO:01001308.definition: A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water held in shape or sustained by an environmental process.

ENVO:01000819.label: hydrosphere
ENVO:01000819.definition: An astronomical body part which is composed of the combined mass of water found on, under, and over the surface of a planet.

ENVO:01000755.label: aeroform
ENVO:01000755.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of gaseous or aerosolised material held in shape by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:01001478.label: gaseous astronomical body part
ENVO:01001478.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:01001477.label: liquid astronomical body part
ENVO:01001477.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:00000287.label: butte
ENVO:00000287.definition: An isolated hill with steep sides and a small flat top, smaller than mesas and plateaus. Buttes are formed by erosion when a cap of hard rock, usually of volcanic origin, covers a layer of softer rock that is easily worn away. This hard rock avoids erosion while the rock around it wears down.

ENVO:01000724.label: condensation process
ENVO:01000724.definition: Condensation is a process during which a gas undergoes a phase transition into a liquid.

ENVO:02500027.label: anthropogenic environmental process
ENVO:02500027.definition: An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans.

ENVO:02500031.label: hydrological process
ENVO:02500031.definition: An environmental process which has water - in any of its states - as a participant.

ENVO:02500003.label: atmospheric process
ENVO:02500003.definition: A process which occurs within an atmosphere.

ENVO:02500001.label: desertification
ENVO:02500001.definition: a type of land degradation in which a relatively dry land region becomes increasingly arid, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.

ENVO:1000748.label: island formation process
ENVO:1000748.definition: A process which results in the formation of an island.

ENVO:03000009.label: material accumulation process
ENVO:03000009.definition: A process during which the mass of one or more materials, present within a given site, increases.

ENVO:03000043.label: material transformation process
ENVO:03000043.definition: A process during which a portion of some environmental material is converted into a different material or a collection of materials.

ENVO:03000010.label: material transport process
ENVO:03000010.definition: A process during which material is displaced from its original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location.

ENVO:01001023.label: radiation
ENVO:01001023.definition: A process during which energy is emitted or transmitted in the form of waves or particles through space or a material medium.

ENVO:01000705.label: soil degradation
ENVO:01000705.definition: Soil degradation is a process which results in a change in soil health status resulting in a diminished capacity of the ecosystem in which the soil occurs to provide goods and services for its  beneficiaries.

ENVO:01001210.label: defence against flooding
ENVO:01001210.definition: A planned process during which an environmental system is modified to mitigate or nullify the impacts of flooding.

ENVO:01001434.label: anthropogenic ecosystem conversion process
ENVO:01001434.definition: A process during which an ecosystem - natural or anthropised - is changed by the actions of humans.

ENVO:01000706.label: soil erosion
ENVO:01000706.definition: Soil erosion is a process in which exogenic processes remove soil from one location on the Earth's crust and transport it to another location where it is deposited.

ENVO:02500002.label: flooding
ENVO:02500002.definition: A general and temporary condition of partial or complete inundation of normally dry land areas from the overflow of inland and/or tidal waters, and/or the unusual and rapid accumulation or runoff of surface waters from any source. A great flow along a watercourse or a flow causing inundation of lands not normally covered by water.

AGRO:00000199.label: percolation process in soil
AGRO:00000199.definition: Hydrological process in which water move through soil and permeable rocks.

ENVO:01000634.label: volcanic eruption
ENVO:01000634.definition: A volcanic process is a process during which lava, tephra (ash, lapilli, volcanic bombs and blocks), and assorted gases are expelled from a volcanic vent or fissure.

ENVO:03000036.label: sedimentation in a water body
ENVO:03000036.definition: A material accumulation process during which solid particles are pulled through a water body by gravitation or centrifugal force and which ends when they settle on a solid surface.

ENVO:01001334.label: advective transport process
ENVO:01001334.definition: A material transport process during which a volume of material is displaced due to a disequilibrium in physical forces and during which 1) the qualities that inhere in that volume and 2) the processes that are unfolding within it are largely unchanged.

ENVO:03000020.label: aeolian transport process
ENVO:03000020.definition: A material transport process during which one or more environmental materials are transported by the action of wind.

ENVO:01001346.label: erosion
ENVO:01001346.definition: An action of exogenic processes (such as water flow or wind) which remove environmental material from one location on the surface of an astronomical body, transporting it to another location where it is deposited.

ENVO:01000875.label: precipitation process
ENVO:01000875.definition: A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force.

ENVO:01001367.label: primary aerosol formation process
ENVO:01001367.definition: A material transport process during which solid or liquid particles are directly introduced into a volume of gas.

ENVO:01001093.label: tectonic movement
ENVO:01001093.definition: A process during which pieces of a planetary crust and uppermost mantle move.

ENVO:01001205.label: lithification
ENVO:01001205.definition: A process during which sediments compact under pressure, expel connate fluids, and gradually become solid sedimentary rock.

ENVO:01001510.label: material congelation process
ENVO:01001510.definition: A material transformation process during which a material's viscosity increase either through a reduction in temperature or through chemical reactions.

ENVO:01000840.label: thermolysis
ENVO:01000840.definition: A chemical decomposition (the separation of a single chemical compound into its two or more elemental parts or to simpler compounds) caused by heat.

FOODON:00001262.label: botanical fruit food product
FOODON:00001262.definition: Mature ovary of a plant, with a fleshy part of the carpel that develops with the seed to attract animals for aid in dispersal. Botanically, nuts are considered fruits.

FOODON:03460177.label: plant seed or nut food product

FOODON:00001261.label: vegetable food product
FOODON:00001261.definition: Any plant food product which, typically, is constituted by intact parts from one or more annual plants cultivated as field and garden crops in the open and under glass, and used almost exclusively for food.

FOODON:03411134.label: mammal
FOODON:03411134.definition: Mammals (from Latin mamma "breast") are vertebrate animals constituting the class Mammalia, and characterized by the presence of mammary glands which in females produce milk for feeding (nursing) their young, a neocortex (a region of the brain), fur or hair, and three middle ear bones.

FOODON:00003194.label: vegetarian food product
FOODON:00003194.definition: A food product not including meat and animal tissue products (such as gelatin or animal-derived rennet).

FOODON:00001092.label: vertebrate animal food product
FOODON:00001092.definition: A food product which is derived from or produced by an animal that has a vertibrae.

FOODON:00001002.label: foodon product type
FOODON:00001002.definition: A substance, usually composed primarily of carbohydrates, fats, water and/or proteins, that can be eaten or drunk by an animal or human being for nutrition or pleasure.

FOODON:03460111.label: food treatment process
FOODON:03460111.definition: Used to specifically characterize a food product based on the treatment or processes applied to the product or any indexed ingredient. The processes include adding, substituting or removing components or modifying the food or component, e.g., through fermentation. Multiple values can be assigned.

ENVO:09200006.label: concentration of ammonium in soil
ENVO:09200006.definition: The concentration of a ammonium when measured in soil.

ENVO:3100004.label: concentration of ammonium in water
ENVO:3100004.definition: The concentration of ammonium when measured in water.

ENVO:3100011.label: concentration of dioxygen in water
ENVO:3100011.definition: The concentration of dioxygen when measured in water.

ENVO:09200007.label: concentration of nitrate in soil
ENVO:09200007.definition: The concentration of a nitrate when measured in soil.

ENVO:3100022.label: concentration of nitrate in water
ENVO:3100022.definition: The concentration of nitrate when measured in water.

ENVO:09200021.label: concentration of oxygen in water
ENVO:09200021.definition: The concentration of a oxygen when measured in water.

FOODON:00002452.label: invertebrate animal
FOODON:00002452.definition: Invertebrates are animals that neither possess nor develop a vertebral column (commonly known as a backbone or spine), derived from the notochord. This includes all animals apart from the subphylum Vertebrata.

FOODON:03411297.label: vertebrate animal
FOODON:03411297.definition: A vertebrate animal is any species of organism within the subphylum Vertebrata (chordates with backbones). Vertebrates represent the overwhelming majority of the phylum Chordata, with currently about 69,276 species described.

FOODON:03400149.label: milled grain or starch product (us cfr)
FOODON:03400149.definition: Food product prepared by milling a grain or by producing flour, meal or grits from a non-grain source such as beans, starchy roots or tubers. Refined starch is indexed under *REFINED OR PARTIALLY REFINED FOOD PRODUCT*.

FOODON:03400152.label: vegetable or vegetable product (us cfr)
FOODON:03400152.definition: Vegetables in all forms except where a use-related product type descriptior (such as *PREPARED FOOD PRODUCT* or *SNACK FOOD*) takes precedence.

FOODON:03401270.label: product type, U.S. code of federal regulations, title 21
FOODON:03401270.definition: Food and Drugs, title 21, Code of Federal Regulations. Original  food classification in LanguaL.

FOODON:03400260.label: nut or nut product (us cfr)
FOODON:03400260.definition: Nuts in all forms, including nut butters and pastes.

FOODON:03400289.label: product type, USA
FOODON:03400289.definition: Food group having common consumption, functional or manufacturing characteristics, e.g. *FRUIT OR VEGETABLE PRODUCT*, *DAIRY PRODUCT*, *CONFECTIONARY*, *PREPARED FOOD PRODUCT*, etc. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

FOODON:03400257.label: fruit or vegetable product (us cfr)
FOODON:03400257.definition: Fruits and vegetables in all forms. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

FOODON:03400125.label: grain or starch product (us cfr)
FOODON:03400125.definition: Any form of whole or milled grain, prepared grain product or starch containing product derived from non-grain sources. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

FOODON:03411452.label: soybean plant
FOODON:03411452.definition: The soybean or soya bean (Glycine max) is a species of legume native to East Asia, widely grown for its edible bean, which has numerous uses.  Traditional unfermented food uses of soybeans include soy milk, from  which tofu and tofu skin are made. Fermented soy foods include soy sauce, fermented bean paste, nattō, and tempeh.

FOODON:03411607.label: nut or edible seed producing plant

FOODON:03411156.label: pod or seed vegetable plant
FOODON:03411156.definition: A legume  is a plant or its fruit or seed in the family *Fabaceae* (or *Leguminosae*). Legumes are grown agriculturally, primarily for their grain seed called pulse, for livestock forage and silage, and as soil-enhancing green manure. Well-known legumes include alfalfa, clover, peas, beans, chickpeas, lentils, lupin bean, mesquite, carob, soybeans, peanuts and tamarind. [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legume]

FOODON:03411567.label: bean plant
FOODON:03411567.definition: A bean plant is one of several genera of the flowering plant family Fabaceae, which has seed pods, seeds, and/or leaf material used for human or animal food.

FOODON:03411013.label: plant used for producing extract or concentrate

FOODON:00003004.label: animal
FOODON:00003004.definition: A multicellular eukaryotic heterotrophic organism within the kingdom Animalia.

FOODON:03411347.label: obsolete: plant
FOODON:03411347.definition: A multicellular eukaryote organism of the kingdom Plantae.

FOODON:03420293.label: fruit core (anatomical part)
FOODON:03420293.definition: The hard, central part of an apple, pear, etc., that contains the seeds (Source: Webster's)

FOODON:03420174.label: part of plant
FOODON:03420174.definition: Anatomical part of a plant, such as fruit, seed, pod, leaf, stem or flower as well as the whole plant.

FOODON:03420155.label: seed (anatomical part)
FOODON:03420155.definition: The main propagative part of a plant, especially the kernel of a grain or nut. The bulk of the seed is formed by the endosperm, which encloses the germ and is covered by skin (bran).

FOODON:03000001.label: food peeling process
FOODON:03000001.definition: "peeling" is the process of removing the outer covering, layer or skin from a fruit, vegetable, or plant or animal (such as a shrimp).

GO:0005488.label: binding
GO:0005488.definition: The selective, non-covalent, often stoichiometric, interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

GO:0098772.label: molecular function regulator
GO:0098772.definition: A molecular function that modulates the activity of a gene product or complex.  Examples include enzyme regulators and channel regulators.

GO:0048018.label: receptor ligand activity
GO:0048018.definition: The activity of a gene product that interacts with a receptor to effect a change in the activity of the receptor. Ligands may be produced by the same, or different, cell that expresses the receptor. Ligands may diffuse extracellularly from their point of origin to the receiving cell, or remain attached to an adjacent cell surface (e.g. Notch ligands).

GO:0005515.label: protein binding
GO:0005515.definition: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein or protein complex (a complex of two or more proteins that may include other nonprotein molecules).

GO:0005102.label: signaling receptor binding
GO:0005102.definition: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with one or more specific sites on a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.

GO:0065007.label: biological regulation
GO:0065007.definition: Any process that modulates a measurable attribute of any biological process, quality or function.

GO:0009987.label: cellular process
GO:0009987.definition: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

OGMS:0000063.label: disease course
OGMS:0000063.definition: The totality of all processes through which a given disease instance is realized.

GO:0050896.label: response to stimulus
GO:0050896.definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell or organism.

GO:0023052.label: signaling
GO:0023052.definition: The entirety of a process in which information is transmitted within a biological system. This process begins with an active signal and ends when a cellular response has been triggered.

GO:0007154.label: cell communication
GO:0007154.definition: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

GO:0051716.label: cellular response to stimulus
GO:0051716.definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus by a cell and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell.

GO:0007165.label: signal transduction
GO:0007165.definition: The cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell. Signal transduction begins with reception of a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a receptor or receptor activation by a stimulus such as light), or for signal transduction in the absence of ligand, signal-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. Signal transduction ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. regulation of transcription or regulation of a metabolic process. Signal transduction covers signaling from receptors located on the surface of the cell and signaling via molecules located within the cell. For signaling between cells, signal transduction is restricted to events at and within the receiving cell.

GO:0009966.label: regulation of signal transduction
GO:0009966.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

GO:0030546.label: signaling receptor activator activity
GO:0030546.definition: The function of interacting (directly or indirectly) with receptors such that the proportion of receptors in the active form is increased.

GO:1900120.label: regulation of receptor binding
GO:1900120.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

GO:0050794.label: regulation of cellular process
GO:0050794.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

GO:0048583.label: regulation of response to stimulus
GO:0048583.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

GO:0023051.label: regulation of signaling
GO:0023051.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

GO:0010646.label: regulation of cell communication
GO:0010646.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

GO:0043393.label: regulation of protein binding
GO:0043393.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

GO:0050789.label: regulation of biological process
GO:0050789.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

GO:0065009.label: regulation of molecular function
GO:0065009.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

GO:0051098.label: regulation of binding
GO:0051098.definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of binding, the selective interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

GO:0030545.label: receptor regulator activity
GO:0030545.definition: The function of interacting (directly or indirectly) with receptors such that the proportion of receptors in the active form is changed.

UO:0000051.label: concentration unit
UO:0000051.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

UO:0000105.label: frequency unit
UO:0000105.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of repetitive actions in a particular time.

UO:0000001.label: length unit
UO:0000001.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

UO:0000002.label: mass unit
UO:0000002.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of matter/energy of a physical object.

UO:0000280.label: rate unit
UO:0000280.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement occurrence of a process per unit time.

UO:0000006.label: substance unit
UO:0000006.definition: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

UO:0000005.label: temperature unit
UO:0000005.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

UO:0000003.label: time unit
UO:0000003.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

UO:0000095.label: volume unit
UO:0000095.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

UO:0000270.label: volumetric flow rate unit
UO:0000270.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

OBI:0000684.label: specimen collection objective
OBI:0000684.definition: A objective specification to obtain a material entity for potential use as an input during an investigation.

OBI:0000962.label: training objective
OBI:0000962.definition: An objective specification which is fulfilled by the provision of some training.

OBI:0000441.label: assay objective
OBI:0000441.definition: an objective specification to determine a specified type of information about an evaluated entity (the material entity bearing evaluant role)

OBI:0000015.label: biological feature identification objective
OBI:0000015.definition: Biological_feature_identification_objective is an objective role carried out by the proposition defining the aim of a study designed to examine or characterize a particular biological feature.

OBI:0200166.label: data transformation objective
OBI:0200166.definition: An objective specification to transformation input data into output data

OBI:0000456.label: material transformation objective
OBI:0000456.definition: an objective specifiction that creates an specific output object from input materials.

OBI:0001175.label: selective organism creation objective
OBI:0001175.definition: an objective specification to generate a population or type of organism within species that have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms.

OBI:0000963.label: categorical label
OBI:0000963.definition: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

IAO:0000003.label: measurement unit label
IAO:0000003.definition: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

OBI:0000713.label: GenePattern software
OBI:0000713.definition: a software that provides access to more than 100 tools for gene expression analysis, proteomics, SNP analysis and common data processing tasks.

OBI:0000679.label: average value
OBI:0000679.definition: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

OBI:0000674.label: center value
OBI:0000674.definition: A data item that is produced as the output of a center calculation data transformation and represents the center value of the input data.

IAO:0000102.label: data about an ontology part
IAO:0000102.definition: data about an ontology part is a data item about a part of an ontology, for example a term

IAO:0000100.label: data set
IAO:0000100.definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

IAO:0000109.label: measurement datum
IAO:0000109.definition: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

OBI:0001909.label: conclusion based on data
OBI:0001909.definition: An information content entity that is inferred from data.

OBI:0001933.label: value specification
OBI:0001933.definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

IAO:0000027.label: data item
IAO:0000027.definition: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

IAO:0000009.label: datum label
IAO:0000009.definition: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

IAO:0000033.label: directive information entity
IAO:0000033.definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

IAO:0000310.label: document
IAO:0000310.definition: A collection of information content entities intended to be understood together as a whole

IAO:0000308.label: figure
IAO:0000308.definition: An information content entity consisting of a two dimensional arrangement of information content entities such that the arrangement itself is about something.

OBI:0001554.label: rate measurement datum
OBI:0001554.definition: A scalar measurement datum that represents the number of events occuring over a time interval

IAO:0000408.label: length measurement datum
IAO:0000408.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

IAO:0000414.label: mass measurement datum
IAO:0000414.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

IAO:0000416.label: time measurement datum
IAO:0000416.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

OBI:0000969.label: dose specification
OBI:0000969.definition: a directive information entity that describes the dose that will be administered to a target

IAO:0000007.label: action specification
IAO:0000007.definition: a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

IAO:0000098.label: data format specification
IAO:0000098.definition:
A data format specification is the information content borne by the document published defining the specification.
Example: The ISO document specifying what encompasses an XML document; The instructions in a XSD file

IAO:0000005.label: objective specification
IAO:0000005.definition: a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

IAO:0000104.label: plan specification
IAO:0000104.definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

OBI:0000750.label: study design independent variable
OBI:0000750.definition: a directive information entity that is part of a study design. Independent variables are entities whose values are selected to determine its relationship to an observed phenomenon (the dependent variable). In such an experiment, an attempt is made to find evidence that the values of the independent variable determine the values of the dependent variable (that which is being measured). The independent variable can be changed as required, and its values do not represent a problem requiring explanation in an analysis, but are taken simply as given. The dependent variable on the other hand, usually cannot be directly controlled

IAO:0000183.label: dendrogram
IAO:0000183.definition:
A dendrogram is a report graph which is a tree diagram
frequently used to illustrate the arrangement of the clusters produced by a
clustering algorithm.

IAO:0000037.label: dot plot
IAO:0000037.definition: A dot plot is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data where each data point is represented by a single dot placed on coordinates corresponding to data point values in particular dimensions.

IAO:0000180.label: heatmap
IAO:0000180.definition:
A heatmap is a report graph which is a graphical representation of data
where the values taken by a variable(s) are shown as colors in a
two-dimensional map.

IAO:0000179.label: histogram
IAO:0000179.definition:
A histogram is a report graph which is a statistical description of a
distribution in terms of occurrence frequencies of different event classes.

IAO:0000184.label: scatter plot
IAO:0000184.definition: A scatterplot is a graph which uses Cartesian coordinates to display values for two variables for a set of data. The data is displayed as a collection of points, each having the value of one variable determining the position on the horizontal axis and the value of the other variable determining the position on the vertical axis.

OBI:0000023.label: classified data set
OBI:0000023.definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class prediction data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned class labels.

OBI:0000648.label: clustered data set
OBI:0000648.definition: A data set that is produced as the output of a class discovery data transformation and consists of a data set with assigned discovered class labels.

IAO:0000409.label: denotator type
IAO:0000409.definition: A denotator type indicates how a term should be interpreted from an ontological perspective.

IAO:0000078.label: curation status specification
IAO:0000078.definition: The curation status of the term. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000225.label: obsolescence reason specification
IAO:0000225.definition: The reason for which a term has been deprecated. The allowed values come from an enumerated list of predefined terms. See the specification of these instances for more detailed definitions of each enumerated value.

IAO:0000064.label: algorithm
