IAO:0000064.definition: A plan specification which describes the inputs and output of mathematical functions as well as workflow of execution for achieving an predefined objective. Algorithms are realized usually by means of implementation as computer programs for execution by automata.

AGRO:00000036.label: application method
AGRO:00000036.definition: A plan specification which describes how a material entity is applied to another material entity.

AGRO:00000054.label: irrigation method
AGRO:00000054.definition: A plan specification which describes how water is applied to plants or soil.

AGRO:00000350.label: planting distribution
AGRO:00000350.definition: Pattern used to plant crop in field.

OBI:0000272.label: protocol
OBI:0000272.definition: A plan specification which has sufficient level of detail and quantitative information to communicate it between investigation agents, so that different investigation agents will reliably be able to independently reproduce the process.

IAO:0000010.label: software
IAO:0000010.definition:
Software is a plan specification composed of a series of instructions that can be 
interpreted by or directly executed by a processing unit.

OBI:0500000.label: study design
OBI:0500000.definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

OBI:0001620.label: latitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001620.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

OBI:0001621.label: longitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001621.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

IAO:0000032.label: scalar measurement datum
IAO:0000032.definition: a scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

IAO:0000309.label: diagram
IAO:0000309.definition: A figure that expresses one or more propositions

IAO:0000101.label: image
IAO:0000101.definition: An image is an affine projection to a two dimensional surface, of measurements of some quality of an entity or entities repeated at regular intervals across a spatial range, where the measurements are represented as color and luminosity on the projected on surface.

IAO:0000038.label: graph
IAO:0000038.definition: A diagram that presents one or more tuples of information by mapping those tuples in to a two dimensional space in a non arbitrary way.

OBI:0001000.label: questionnaire
OBI:0001000.definition: A document with a set of printed or written questions with a choice of answers, devised for the purposes of a survey or statistical study.

OBI:0001167.label: age measurement datum
OBI:0001167.definition: A time measurement datum that is the result of measurement of age of an organism

NCBITaxon:91561.label: Artiodactyla
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: whales, hippos, ruminants, pigs, camels etc.

ENVO:02500026.label: anthropogenic modulatory intervention process
ENVO:02500026.definition: A process during which humans apply technology to alter the magnitude, duration, rate, or impact of an environmental process.

OBI:0000659.label: specimen collection process
OBI:0000659.definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

OBI:0000471.label: study design execution
OBI:0000471.definition: a planned process that carries out a study design

OBI:0000931.label: study intervention
OBI:0000931.definition: the part of the execution of an intervention design study which is varied between two or more subjects in the study

OBI:0000939.label: training process
OBI:0000939.definition: a process that achieves a training objective

AGRO:00002071.label: agricultural process
AGRO:00002071.definition: A planned process which occurs during an agricultural experiment.

OBI:0000070.label: assay
OBI:0000070.definition: A planned process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies.

OBI:0200000.label: data transformation
OBI:0200000.definition: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

OBI:0200111.label: data visualization
OBI:0200111.definition: An planned process that creates images, diagrams or animations from the input data.

IAO:0000572.label: documenting
IAO:0000572.definition: a planned process in which a document is created or added to by including the specified input in it.

OBI:0000338.label: drawing a conclusion based on data
OBI:0000338.definition: A planned process in which data gathered in an investigation is evaluated in the context of existing knowledge with the objective to generate more general conclusions or to conclude that the data does not allow one to draw general conclusion

AGRO:00000369.label: experiment
AGRO:00000369.definition: A planned process in which a procedure is carried out to support, refute, or validate a hypothesis.

OBI:0000066.label: investigation
OBI:0000066.definition: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

OBI:0000094.label: material processing
OBI:0000094.definition: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material

AGRO:00000349.label: soil analysis process
AGRO:00000349.definition: A planned process in which an analysis of soil is performed to determine soil characteristics.

OBI:0000268.label: organism feature identification objective
OBI:0000268.definition: Organism_feature_identification_objective is a biological_feature_identification_objective role describing a study designed to examine or characterize a biological feature monitored at the level of the organism, e.g. height, weight, stage of development, stage of life cycle.

OBI:0000014.label: regulator role
OBI:0000014.definition: a regulatory role involved with making and/or enforcing relevant legislation and governmental orders

OBI:0000953.label: processed specimen
OBI:0000953.definition: A specimen that has been intentionally physically modified.

OBI:0000652.label: material combination
OBI:0000652.definition: is a material processing with the objective to combine two or more material entities as input into a single material entity as output.

OBI:0000457.label: manufacturing
OBI:0000457.definition: Manufacturing is a process with the intent to produce a processed material which will have a function for future use. A person or organization (having manufacturer role) is a participant in this process

OBI:0000740.label: material sample role
OBI:0000740.definition: A material sample role is a specimen role borne by a material entity that is the output of a material sampling process.

OBI:0000828.label: research organization
OBI:0000828.definition: An organization formed with a goal to have its members conduct investigations

OBI:0001942.label: grant agency
OBI:0001942.definition: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

OBI:0000450.label: regulatory agency
OBI:0000450.definition: A regulatory agency is a organization that has responsibility over or for  the legislation (acts and regulations) for a given sector of the government.

AGRO:00000255.label: agricultural process depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000255.definition: Measurement protocol in which the depth into the soil of an agricultural process is measured.

AGRO:00000286.label: area measurement protocol
AGRO:00000286.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure a field area.

AGRO:00000252.label: bund height measurement protocol
AGRO:00000252.definition: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of a bund. Repeat this operation on multiple bunds, and average the results.

AGRO:00000258.label: chemical concentration in fertilizer recording protocol
AGRO:00000258.definition: Record the concentration of the chemical element of interest in the fertilizer used indicated on the fertilizer container.

AGRO:00000275.label: determination of organic carbon protocol
AGRO:00000275.definition: Protocol used to determine the content of organic carbon in environmental material.

AGRO:00000274.label: determination of organic nitrogen in environmental material protocol
AGRO:00000274.definition: Protocol used to determine the content of organic nitrogen in environmental material.

AGRO:00000295.label: environmental material incorporation percentage measurement protocol
AGRO:00000295.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of incorporation in soil of an environmental material.

AGRO:00000259.label: harvested row counting protocol
AGRO:00000259.definition: Count the number of row that have been harvested.

AGRO:00000248.label: interrow width measurement protocol
AGRO:00000248.definition: With a ruler measure the distance between the center of two rows. The center of the rows is where the plant reproductive material has been planted.

AGRO:00000280.label: irrigation equipment depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000280.definition: Measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the irrigation equipment buried in soil.

AGRO:00000284.label: irrigation water quantity recording protocol
AGRO:00000284.definition: Record the quantity of water used for irrigation.

AGRO:00000264.label: lignin concentration measurement protocol
AGRO:00000264.definition: Protocol in which the lignin concentration of an environmental material is measured.

AGRO:00000242.label: material area density mesurement protocol
AGRO:00000242.definition: Protocol used to measure the area density of a material.

AGRO:00000251.label: moisture concentration measurement protocol
AGRO:00000251.definition: 1.Weight a sample of the material. 2.Dry this sample. 3.Weight the dry sample. Moisture concentration = ((Ww-Wd)/Ww) x 100 in which : WW = wet weight of the sample, and Wd = weight of the sample after drying.

AGRO:00000278.label: mulch color recording protocol
AGRO:00000278.definition: Record the color of the mulch applied.

AGRO:00000247.label: mulch thickness measurement protocol
AGRO:00000247.definition: With a ruler measure the distance between the soil surface and the top of the mulch layer.

AGRO:00000449.label: nitrogen recovery efficiency measurement protocol
AGRO:00000449.definition: Calculate the amount of nitrogen in the crop as a ratio of the amount of nitrogen applied or available.

AGRO:00000451.label: nitrogen use efficiency measurement protocol
AGRO:00000451.definition: Calculate the ratio between the amount of nitrogen fertilizer removed with the crop and the amount of nitrogen fertilizer applied.

AGRO:00000285.label: percolation test protocol
AGRO:00000285.definition: Protocol in which the rapidity at which water moves through soil is measured.

AGRO:00000283.label: pest control agent released density recording protocol
AGRO:00000283.definition: Record the number of pest control agent released per surface area.

AGRO:00000282.label: pivot lenght measurement protocol
AGRO:00000282.definition: Measure the lenght of the pivot.

AGRO:00000262.label: plant density measurement protocol
AGRO:00000262.definition: Protocol that describes how to count the number of plants in a known area.

AGRO:00000263.label: row length mesurement protocol
AGRO:00000263.definition: Measure the distance between the beginning and the end of the row.

AGRO:00000290.label: soil coverage by environmental material measurement protocol
AGRO:00000290.definition: Protocol that describes how to measure the percentage of soil coverage by environmental material like mulch or crop residue.

AGRO:00000249.label: sprout lenght measurement protocol
AGRO:00000249.definition: Measure the length of sprout with a steel tape.

AGRO:00000294.label: total quantity of environmental material used compute protocol
AGRO:00000294.definition: Add all the quantities of the environmental material of interest applied over a specified period.

AGRO:00000277.label: tractor speed recording protocol
AGRO:00000277.definition: Record the speed of the tractor in the field.

AGRO:00000279.label: transplant age counting protocol
AGRO:00000279.definition: Protocol in which the age of the transplant is determined by counting the number of days between the seeding date and the transplanting date.

AGRO:00000250.label: water source distance measurement protocol
AGRO:00000250.definition: Measure the shortest distance between the water source and the entrance of the field with a measuring wheel.

AGRO:00000281.label: well depth measurement protocol
AGRO:00000281.definition: Tie a small but heavy weight to the end of a piece of string. Lower the weight into the well until it reaches the bottom. Take up the slack and mark the string at ground level. Pull the weight out of the well and measure from the bottom of the weight to the ground level mark. This is the depth of the well.

OBI:0600007.label: administering substance in vivo
OBI:0600007.definition: A process by which a substance is intentionally given to an organism resulting in exposure of the organism to that substance.

OBI:0000686.label: material combination objective
OBI:0000686.definition: is an objective to obtain an output material that contains several input materials.

OBI:0001153.label: genetic transformation objective
OBI:0001153.definition: a material transformation objective aims to create genetically modified organism or cell

OBI:0000458.label: manufacturing objective
OBI:0000458.definition: is the objective to manufacture a material of a certain function (device)

OBI:0000274.label: adding a material entity into a target
OBI:0000274.definition: is a process with the objective to place a material entity bearing the 'material to be added role' into a material bearing the 'target of material addition role'.

OBI:0000744.label: material sampling process
OBI:0000744.definition: A specimen gathering process with the objective to obtain a specimen that is representative of the input material entity

OBI:0000700.label: support vector machine
OBI:0000700.definition: A support vector machine is a data transformation with a class prediction objective based on the construction of a separating hyperplane that maximizes the margin between two data sets of vectors in n-dimensional space.

OBI:0000434.label: adding material objective
OBI:0000434.definition: is the specification of an objective to add a material into a target material. The adding is asymmetric in the sense that the target material largely retains its identity

OBI:0000749.label: CART
OBI:0000749.definition: A CART (classification and regression trees) is a data transformation method for producing a classification or regression model with a tree-based structure.

OBI:0200033.label: leave one out cross validation method
OBI:0200033.definition: is a data transformation :  leave-one-out cross-validation (LOOCV) involves using a single observation from the original sample as the validation data, and the remaining observations as the training data. This is repeated such that each observation in the sample is used once as the validation data

OBI:0000018.label: material supplier role
OBI:0000018.definition: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

OBI:0302716.label: pool of specimens
OBI:0302716.definition: A pool of specimens is a mixture of a population of samples which have been gathered from one or more sample populations, obtained by the physical process of mixing individual specimens, e.g.  mixing the DNA collected from the individual fish.

OBI:0001161.label: age since germination measurement datum
OBI:0001161.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since germination, the process consisting of physiological and developmental changes by a seed, spore, pollen grain (microspore), or zygote that occur after release from dormancy, and encompassing events prior to and including the first visible indications of growth.

OBI:0001156.label: age since planting measurement datum
OBI:0001156.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since planting, the process of placing a plant in media (e.g. soil) to allow it to grow, which excludes sowing.

OBI:0001164.label: age since sowing measurement datum
OBI:0001164.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since sowing, the process of placing a seed or spore in some media with the intention to invoke germination.

OBI:0002326.label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics cervical cancer stage value specification
OBI:0002326.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a gynecologic cancer according to the International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging systems.

OBI:0002341.label: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics ovarian cancer stage value specification
OBI:0002341.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the FIGO classification system.

OBI:0002314.label: clinical tumor stage group according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002314.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of the stage of a cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) v7 staging systems.

OBI:0002205.label: histologic grade according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002205.definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) 7th Edition grading system.

OBI:0002210.label: histologic grade according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System
OBI:0002210.definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a tumor slide specimen according to the Fuhrman Nuclear Grading System.

OBI:0002215.label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor
OBI:0002215.definition: A categorical value specification that is a histologic grade assigned to a ovarian tumor.

OBI:0002290.label: pathologic distant metastases stage for colon according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002290.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colon cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002306.label: pathologic distant metastases stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002306.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002298.label: pathologic distant metastases stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002298.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002310.label: pathologic distant metastases stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002310.definition: A categorical value specification that is a  pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases. TNM pathologic distant metastasis findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002270.label: pathologic lymph node stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002270.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

OBI:0002284.label: pathologic lymph node stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002284.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

OBI:0002279.label: pathologic lymph node stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002279.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

OBI:0002287.label: pathologic lymph node stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002287.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

OBI:0002224.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for colon and rectum according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002224.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of colorectal cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002243.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for kidney according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002243.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of renal cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002232.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for lung according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002232.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of lung cancer following the rules of the TNM American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC) version 7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002256.label: pathologic primary tumor stage for ovary according to AJCC 7th edition
OBI:0002256.definition: A categorical value specification that is a pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of ovarian cancer following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor. TNM pathologic primary tumor findings are based on clinical findings supplemented by histopathologic examination of one or more tissue specimens acquired during surgery.

OBI:0002356.label: performance status value specification
OBI:0002356.definition: A categorical value specification that is an assessment of a participant's performance status (general well-being and activities of daily life).

OBI:0001930.label: categorical value specification
OBI:0001930.definition: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories

OBI:0001931.label: scalar value specification
OBI:0001931.definition: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

OBI:0002216.label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to a two-tier grading system
OBI:0002216.definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a two-tier histological classification of tumors.

OBI:0002219.label: histologic grade for ovarian tumor according to the World Health Organization
OBI:0002219.definition: A histologic grade for ovarian tumor that is from a histological classification by the World Health Organization (WHO).

OBI:0002357.label: Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group score value specification
OBI:0002357.definition: A performance status value specification designed by the Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group to assess disease progression and its affect on the daily living abilities of the patient.

OBI:0002363.label: Karnofsky score vaue specification
OBI:0002363.definition: A performance status value specification designed for classifying patients 16 years of age or older by their functional impairment.

AGRO:00000325.label: crop
AGRO:00000325.definition: A crop is any cultivated plant, fungus, or alga that is harvested for food, clothing, livestock,fodder, biofuel, medicine, or other uses

AGRO:00000116.label: draft animal
AGRO:00000116.definition: Organism used to pull agricultural implements.

OBI:0001185.label: selectively maintained organism
OBI:0001185.definition: An organism that is bred to have some uniform behavioral, morphological, physiological, or genetic characteristics with similarly bred organisms

OBI:0000747.label: material sample
OBI:0000747.definition: A material entity that has the material sample role

OBI:0000726.label: peak matching
OBI:0000726.definition: Peak matching is a data transformation performed on a dataset of a graph of ordered data points (e.g. a spectrum) with the objective of pattern matching local maxima above a noise threshold

OBI:0200170.label: averaging data transformation
OBI:0200170.definition: An averaging data transformation is a data transformation that has objective averaging.

OBI:0200181.label: center calculation data transformation
OBI:0200181.definition: A center calculation data transformation is a data transformation that has objective of center calculation.

OBI:0200175.label: class discovery data transformation
OBI:0200175.definition: A class discovery data transformation (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class discovery.

OBI:0000663.label: class prediction data transformation
OBI:0000663.definition: A class prediction data transformation (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation that has objective class prediction.

OBI:0000707.label: decision tree building data transformation
OBI:0000707.definition: A decision tree building data transformation is a data transformation that has objective decision tree induction.

OBI:0200171.label: partitioning data transformation
OBI:0200171.definition: A partitioning data transformation is a data transformation that has objective partitioning.

OBI:0200051.label: principal components analysis dimensionality reduction
OBI:0200051.definition: A principal components analysis dimensionality reduction is a dimensionality reduction achieved by applying principal components analysis and by keeping low-order principal components and excluding higher-order ones.

OBI:0200190.label: clustered data visualization
OBI:0200190.definition: A data visualization which has input of a clustered data set and produces an output of a report graph which is capable of rendering data of this type.

OBI:0000704.label: decision tree induction objective
OBI:0000704.definition: A decision tree induction objective is a data transformation objective in which a tree-like graph of edges and nodes is created and from which the selection of each branch requires that some type of logical decision is made.

OBI:0000425.label: averaging objective
OBI:0000425.definition: An averaging objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to perform mean calculations on the input of the data transformation.

OBI:0200177.label: center calculation objective
OBI:0200177.definition: A center calculation objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to calculate the center of an input data set.

OBI:0200178.label: class discovery objective
OBI:0200178.definition: A class discovery objective (sometimes called unsupervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to organize input data  (typically vectors of attributes) into classes, where the number of classes and their specifications are not known a priori. Depending on usage, the class assignment can be definite or probabilistic.

OBI:0200179.label: class prediction objective
OBI:0200179.definition:
A class prediction objective (sometimes called supervised classification) is a data transformation objective where the aim is to create a predictor from training data through a machine learning technique. The training data consist of pairs of objects (typically vectors of attributes) and
class labels for these objects. The resulting predictor can be used to attach class labels to any valid novel input object. Depending on usage, the prediction can be definite or probabilistic. A classification is learned from the training data and can then be tested on test data.

OBI:0200172.label: partitioning objective
OBI:0200172.definition: A partitioning objective is a data transformation objective where the aim is to generate a collection of disjoint non-empty subsets whose union equals a non-empty input set.

OBI:0000792.label: statistical model validation
OBI:0000792.definition: A data transformation which assesses how the results of a statistical analysis will generalize to an independent data set.

OBI:0200041.label: k-means clustering
OBI:0200041.definition: A k-means clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, which takes as input a collection of objects (represented as points in multidimensional space) and which partitions them into a specified number k of clusters. The algorithm attempts to find the centers of natural clusters in the data. The most common form of the algorithm starts by partitioning the input points into k initial sets, either at random or using some heuristic data. It then calculates the mean point, or centroid, of each set. It constructs a new partition by associating each point with the closest centroid. Then the centroids are recalculated for the new clusters, and the algorithm repeated by alternate applications of these two steps until convergence, which is obtained when the points no longer switch clusters (or alternatively centroids are no longer changed).

OBI:0000727.label: k-nearest neighbors
OBI:0000727.definition: A k-nearest neighbors is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery or partitioning objective, in which an input data object with vector y is assigned to a class label based upon the k closest training data set points to y; where k is the largest value that class label is assigned.

OBI:0200188.label: cross validation objective
OBI:0200188.definition: A cross validation objective is a data transformation objective in which the aim is to partition a sample of data into subsets such that the analysis is initially performed on a single subset, while the other subset(s) are retained for subsequent use in confirming and validating the initial analysis.

OBI:0200050.label: dimensionality reduction
OBI:0200050.definition: A dimensionality reduction is data partitioning which transforms each input m-dimensional vector (x_1, x_2, ..., x_m) into an output n-dimensional vector (y_1, y_2, ..., y_n), where n is smaller than m.

OBI:0200042.label: hierarchical clustering
OBI:0200042.definition: A hierarchical clustering is a data transformation which achieves a class discovery objective, which takes as input data item and builds a hierarchy of clusters. The traditional representation of this hierarchy is a tree (visualized by a dendrogram), with the individual input objects at one end (leaves) and a single cluster containing every object at the other (root).

AGRO:00000343.label: agronomic experimental design
AGRO:00000343.definition: A plan specification that states how treatments are allocated to the experimental units during an agronomic trial. It refers to the conceptual framework within which the experiment is conducted.

OBI:0001293.label: disease state design
OBI:0001293.definition: A study design in which the pathological condition of a part, organ, or system of an organism is studied. The etiology may be from infection, genetic defect, or environmental stress.

OBI:0000115.label: intervention design
OBI:0000115.definition: An intervention design is a study design in which a controlled process applied to the subjects (the intervention) serves as the independent variable manipulated by the experimentalist. The treatment (perturbation or intervention) defined can be defined as a combination of values taken by independent variable manipulated by the experimentalists are applied to the recruited subjects assigned (possibly by applying specific methods) to treatment groups. The specificity of intervention design is the fact that independent variables are being manipulated and a response of the biological system is evaluated via response variables as monitored by possibly a series of assays.

OBI:0001464.label: strain comparison design
OBI:0001464.definition: A study design that assays differences between multiple strains, cultivars, serovars, isolates, lines from organisms of a single species.

OBI:0500011.label: latin square design
OBI:0500011.definition: Latin square design is_a study design which allows in its simpler form controlling 2 levels of nuisance variables (also known as blocking variables).he 2 nuisance factors are divided into a tabular grid with the property that each row and each column receive each treatment exactly once.

PATO:0001236.label: process quality
PATO:0001236.definition: A quality which inheres in an process.

PATO:0001759.label: granular
PATO:0001759.definition: A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing granules.

PATO:0001842.label: acidity
PATO:0001842.definition: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing acid (hydrogen ions).

ENVO:3100017.label: concentration of hydrogen sulfide in water
ENVO:3100017.definition: The concentration of hydrogen sulfide when measured in water.

PATO:0001655.label: osmolarity
PATO:0001655.definition: A concentration quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of osmoles of solute per liter of solution.

AGRO:00000318.label: distance between rows
AGRO:00000318.definition: Average distance between plants in a same row.

AGRO:00000315.label: plot spacing
AGRO:00000315.definition: Distance quality that represents the distance between two plots.

PATO:0000386.label: hard
PATO:0000386.definition: A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure.

ENVO:09200003.label: atmospheric wind intensity
ENVO:09200003.definition: The intensity of a atmospheric wind.

PATO:0001332.label: amorphous
PATO:0001332.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lack of distinct morphology.

PATO:0000014.label: color
PATO:0000014.definition: A composite chromatic quality composed of hue, saturation and intensity parts.

PATO:0000052.label: shape
PATO:0000052.definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

PATO:0000117.label: size
PATO:0000117.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

PATO:0000060.label: spatial pattern
PATO:0000060.definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting repetition of placement of its parts.

PATO:0000141.label: structure
PATO:0000141.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's relative position, shape, arrangements and connectivity of an organism's various parts; the pattern underlying its form.

PATO:0002005.label: concavity
PATO:0002005.definition: Surface shape that refers to the inward or outward curvature of the surface.

PATO:0001591.label: curvature
PATO:0001591.definition: A surface shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a degree of bending.

PATO:0001154.label: elongated
PATO:0001154.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's length being notably higher than its width.

PATO:0001199.label: linear
PATO:0001199.definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being narrow, with the two opposite margins parallel.

PATO:0001481.label: sloped
PATO:0001481.definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an oblique or slanted direction.

AGRO:00000355.label: slope shape
AGRO:00000355.definition: Shape quality that refers to the general shape of a slope in both vertical and horizontal directions.

AGRO:00010011.label: number of fertilizer applications
AGRO:00010011.definition: The occurrence of a fertilization process

AGRO:00010015.label: number of irrigations
AGRO:00010015.definition: The occurrence of a irrigation process

AGRO:00010018.label: number of weedings
AGRO:00010018.definition: The occurrence of a weeding process

AGRO:00010000.label: total number of land levelling passes
AGRO:00010000.definition: The occurrence of a land levelling process

PATO:0001791.label: multi-localised
PATO:0001791.definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being confined or restricted to multiple locations.

PATO:0002067.label: stratification
PATO:0002067.definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's layered configuration.

PATO:0000070.label: amount
PATO:0000070.definition: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

PATO:0000069.label: deviation(from_normal)
PATO:0000069.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

PATO:0000049.label: intensity
PATO:0000049.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's possessing or displaying a distinctive feature in type or degree or effect or force.

PATO:0002301.label: decreased quality
PATO:0002301.definition: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002300.label: increased quality
PATO:0002300.definition: A quality that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

AGRO:00010005.label: crop residue amount
AGRO:00010005.definition: The amount of a crop residue

AGRO:00010017.label: fertilizer amount
AGRO:00010017.definition: The amount of a agronomic fertilizer

AGRO:00010009.label: inorganic fertilizer amount
AGRO:00010009.definition: The amount of a inorganic fertilizer

AGRO:00010008.label: organic fertilizer amount
AGRO:00010008.definition: The amount of a organic fertilizer

AGRO:00000305.label: number of blocks
AGRO:00000305.definition: Number of block used for an experiment.

AGRO:00000326.label: number of crops
AGRO:00000326.definition: Number of different crop used in an experiment.

AGRO:00000306.label: number of plots
AGRO:00000306.definition: Number of plot used during an experiment.

AGRO:00000310.label: number of pots
AGRO:00000310.definition: Number of pot used during an experiment.

AGRO:00000324.label: number of replications
AGRO:00000324.definition: Number of replications in an experiment.

AGRO:00000323.label: number of treatments
AGRO:00000323.definition: Number of treatments tested during an experiment.

PATO:0001454.label: sensitivity to oxygen
PATO:0001454.definition: A sensitivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's dependence on oxygen.

PATO:0000152.label: threshold
PATO:0000152.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's sensitivity towards a fixed location or value where a change is observed; upper limit.

PATO:0001708.label: 1-D extent
PATO:0001708.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension.

PATO:0001709.label: 2-D extent
PATO:0001709.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.

PATO:0001710.label: 3-D extent
PATO:0001710.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in three dimensions.

PATO:0000587.label: decreased size
PATO:0000587.definition: A size quality which is relatively low.

AGRO:00000441.label: bund height
AGRO:00000441.definition: Height of the small earth embankments which contain irrigation water within basins.

AGRO:00000311.label: pot height
AGRO:00000311.definition: Distance between the top and the bottom of a pot.

AGRO:00000358.label: temperature sensor siting height
AGRO:00000358.definition: Distance between the ground and the temperature sensor.

AGRO:00000359.label: wind speed sensor siting height
AGRO:00000359.definition: Distance between the ground and the wind speed sensor.

AGRO:00000445.label: center pivot irrigation equipment length
AGRO:00000445.definition: Length of the pivot used during the irrigation process.

AGRO:00000356.label: field maximum length
AGRO:00000356.definition: Maximum length of an agromical field.

AGRO:00000010.label: irrigation water quantity
AGRO:00000010.definition: Quantity of water applied per irrigation operation.

AGRO:00000307.label: plot length
AGRO:00000307.definition: A length quality that inheres in the smallest unit of an experiment.

AGRO:00000314.label: row length
AGRO:00000314.definition: A length quality that is the distance between the beginning and the end of a row.

AGRO:00000190.label: tillage tool blade length
AGRO:00000190.definition: A length quality which is equal to the length of the tillage tool that penetrate into the soil.

AGRO:00000446.label: well depth
AGRO:00000446.definition: Distance between the bottom of the well and the soil surface.

AGRO:00010023.label: amount harvested
AGRO:00010023.definition: The mass of a harvested crop

PATO:0001563.label: increased mass
PATO:0001563.definition: A mass which is higher than normal or average.

PATO:0002326.label: angle
PATO:0002326.definition: An orientation inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement at an angle.

AGRO:00000340.label: environmental feature grade
AGRO:00000340.definition: The grade of a physical feature, landform or constructed line refers to the tangent of the angle of that surface to the horizontal.

AGRO:00000320.label: plot orientation
AGRO:00000320.definition: Orientation of the plots in a field.

AGRO:00000319.label: row orientation
AGRO:00000319.definition: Orientation of the rows in a field.

PATO:0001476.label: decreased position
PATO:0001476.definition: A positional which is relatively low.

PATO:0002181.label: displaced
PATO:0002181.definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in position.

PATO:0001687.label: elevation
PATO:0001687.definition: A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical distance of a point above or below a reference surface.

PATO:0001475.label: increased position
PATO:0001475.definition: A position which is relatively high.

PATO:0000133.label: orientation
PATO:0000133.definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

PATO:0001502.label: complexity
PATO:0001502.definition: A monadic quality of continuant inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

PATO:0000025.label: composition
PATO:0000025.definition: A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

PATO:0002124.label: laminar
PATO:0002124.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's processing the form of a thin plate sheet or layer.

PATO:0000970.label: permeability
PATO:0000970.definition: A structural quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being permeated or pervaded by a gas or liquid (as by osmosis or diffusion).

PATO:0001306.label: decreased temperature
PATO:0001306.definition: A temperature which is relatively low.

PATO:0001985.label: frozen
PATO:0001985.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.

PATO:0001305.label: increased temperature
PATO:0001305.definition: A temperature which is relatively high.

ENVO:09200000.label: temperature of environmental material
ENVO:09200000.definition: The temperature of some environmental material.

PATO:0050000.label: rate of occurence
PATO:0050000.definition: The number of repeated events per unit time, occurring in a repeating series. (e.g. the number of heart beats occurring over 1 minute)

PATO:0000011.label: age
PATO:0000011.definition: A time quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of how long the bearer has existed.

PATO:0002201.label: handedness
PATO:0002201.definition: A behavioral quality inhering ina bearer by virtue of the bearer's unequal distribution of fine motor skill between its left and right hands or feet.

PATO:0001701.label: mature
PATO:0001701.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting complete growth, differentiation, or development.

PATO:0001264.label: light yellow
PATO:0001264.definition: A color consisting of yellow hue and high brightness.

PATO:0002253.label: platelike
PATO:0002253.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being roundish, flattish shape, possibly with a slightly angled edge.

PATO:0000592.label: decreased thickness
PATO:0000592.definition: A thickness which is relatively low.

AGRO:00010004.label: crop residue thickness
AGRO:00010004.definition: The thickness of a crop residue

AGRO:00000468.label: field maximum width
AGRO:00000468.definition: Maximum width of an agronomical field.

AGRO:00000308.label: plot width
AGRO:00000308.definition: A width entity that inheres in the smallest unit of an experiment.

AGRO:00000313.label: row width
AGRO:00000313.definition: A width entity that inheres in some row.

PATO:0000963.label: opaque
PATO:0000963.definition: A optical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being clear; not transmitting or reflecting light or radiant energy.

PATO:0000973.label: porosity
PATO:0000973.definition: A permeability quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to admit the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

PATO:0000984.label: porous
PATO:0000984.definition: A porosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being capable of admitting the passage of gas or liquid through pores or interstices.

PATO:0000998.label: viscous
PATO:0000998.definition: A viscosity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having viscosity.

PATO:0015021.label: combustibility
PATO:0015021.definition: The propensity of a material to undergo combustion. Combustion encompasses smouldering and flaming combustion. Combustibility is usually applied to solids.

PATO:0001585.label: conductivity
PATO:0001585.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

PATO:0000039.label: direction
PATO:0000039.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's orientation in space.

PATO:0000040.label: distance
PATO:0000040.definition: A quality that is the extent of space between two entities.

PATO:0001029.label: efficiency
PATO:0001029.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of ratio of the bearer's output to the bearer's input.

PATO:0001464.label: electric potential
PATO:0001464.definition: A quality that is equal to the potential energy per unit charge associated with a static (time-invariant) electric field, also called the electrostatic potential.

PATO:0001021.label: energy
PATO:0001021.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's capacity to do work.

ENVO:01000203.label: environmental condition
ENVO:01000203.definition: An environmental condition is a range of a determinate quality or combination of qualities that are present in an environmental system.

PATO:0001035.label: force
PATO:0001035.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's rate of change of momentum.

PATO:0000125.label: mass
PATO:0000125.definition: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the proportion of the bearer's amount of matter.

PATO:0001019.label: mass density
PATO:0001019.definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size.

PATO:0001906.label: movement quality
PATO:0001906.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's participation in movement.

PATO:0000140.label: position
PATO:0000140.definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

PATO:0001025.label: pressure
PATO:0001025.definition: A physical quality that inheres in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of force per unit area it exerts.

PATO:0001470.label: proportionality to
PATO:0001470.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

PATO:0002198.label: quality of a substance
PATO:0002198.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of its constitution.

PATO:0001739.label: radiation quality
PATO:0001739.definition: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.

PATO:0000146.label: temperature
PATO:0000146.definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

PATO:0000165.label: time
PATO:0000165.definition: A quality in which events occur in sequence.

PATO:0001822.label: wetness
PATO:0001822.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of whether the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

PATO:0001026.label: work
PATO:0001026.definition: A physical quality which is equal to the energy transferred by a force to a moving object.

PATO:0001351.label: area density
PATO:0001351.definition: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given area.

PATO:0001352.label: linear density
PATO:0001352.definition: A density quality which is equal to the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

ENVO:09200005.label: mass density of soil
ENVO:09200005.definition: The mass density of some soil.

PATO:0001353.label: volumetric density
PATO:0001353.definition: A density quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence exerted by the bearer's mass on a given volume.

PATO:0000128.label: weight
PATO:0000128.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer that has mass near a gravitational body.

PATO:0001547.label: quality of a gas
PATO:0001547.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity consisting of particles that have neither a defined volume nor defined shape.

PATO:0001548.label: quality of a liquid
PATO:0001548.definition: A physical quality inhering in an entity exhibiting the physical characteristics of an amorphous (non-crystalline) form of matter between a gas and a solid that has a definite volume, but no definite shape.

PATO:0001546.label: quality of a solid
PATO:0001546.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting the physical characteristics of an entity characterized by particles arranged such that their shape and volume are relatively stable.

PATO:0002303.label: decreased object quality
PATO:0002303.definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0001555.label: has number of
PATO:0001555.definition: The number of parts of a particular type that the bearer entity has. This is a relational quality, and thus holds between two entities: the bearer of the quality, and the type of parts.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: has or lacks parts of type
extra or missing physical or functional parts

PATO:0002305.label: increased object quality
PATO:0002305.definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002182.label: molecular quality
PATO:0002182.definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

PATO:0000051.label: morphology
PATO:0000051.definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

PATO:0001995.label: organismal quality
PATO:0001995.definition: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

PATO:0001018.label: physical quality
PATO:0001018.definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

ENVO:01001164.label: geodiversity
ENVO:01001164.definition: A quality which inheres in a astronomical body or astronomical body part by virtue of the variation in its material composition, participation in geological processes, and the variation in is land- and hydroforms.

PATO:0001292.label: full-spectrum EM radiation quality
PATO:0001292.definition: An EM radiation quality that is independent of the EM wavelength range.

PATO:0001300.label: optical quality
PATO:0001300.definition: An EM radiation quality in which the EM radiation is within the fiat range of the spectrum visible deemed to be light.

PATO:0001294.label: radiation reflective quality
PATO:0001294.definition: A scalar EM radiation quality which obtains by the capacity of the bearer to scatter or reflect radiation.

PATO:0001295.label: albedo
PATO:0001295.definition: A reflective quality restricted to a particular wavelength.

PATO:0000957.label: opacity
PATO:0000957.definition: An optical quality which obtains by virtue of the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.

AGRO:00000488.label: crop rotation duration
AGRO:00000488.definition: A duration inhering in a crop rotation process

AGRO:00010006.label: crop residue percent coverage
AGRO:00010006.definition: The area of a crop residue

AGRO:00000299.label: farm area
AGRO:00000299.definition: An area quality inhering in a farm.

AGRO:00000300.label: field area
AGRO:00000300.definition: An area quality inhering in a field.

AGRO:00000438.label: harvested surface area
AGRO:00000438.definition: Area quality inhering in a surface that have been harvested.

AGRO:00000302.label: plot area
AGRO:00000302.definition: An area quality inhering in a plot.

AGRO:00000440.label: soil organic fertilizer coverage
AGRO:00000440.definition: Area of soil covered by organic fertilizer.

AGRO:00000169.label: ammonium area density
AGRO:00000169.definition: An area density quality which inheres in ammonium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of ammonium applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000178.label: boron area density
AGRO:00000178.definition: An area density quality which inheres in boron by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of boron applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000170.label: calcium area density
AGRO:00000170.definition: An area density quality which inheres in calcium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of calcium applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000166.label: chemical pest control material area density
AGRO:00000166.definition: An area density quality which inheres in chemical pest control material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of chemical pest control material applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000188.label: chlorine area density
AGRO:00000188.definition: An area density quality which inheres in chlorine by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of chlorine applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000177.label: copper area density
AGRO:00000177.definition: An area density quality which inheres in copper by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of copper applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000444.label: crop residue area density
AGRO:00000444.definition: An area density quality which inheres in above-ground crop residue by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of above-ground crop residue applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000200.label: fertilizer area density
AGRO:00000200.definition: An area density quality which inheres in fertilizer by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of fertilizer applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000175.label: iron area density
AGRO:00000175.definition: An area density quality which inheres in iron by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of iron applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000152.label: liming material area density
AGRO:00000152.definition: An area density quality which inheres in liming material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of liming material applied on a given surface area.

AGRO:00000174.label: magnesium area density
AGRO:00000174.definition: An area density quality which inheres in magnesium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of magnesium applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000180.label: manganese area density
AGRO:00000180.definition: An area density quality which inheres in manganese by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of manganese applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000443.label: micronutrients area density
AGRO:00000443.definition: An area density quality which inheres in micronutrients by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of micronutrients applied in a given surface area. Micronutrients for plants are Boron, Chlorine, Iron, Zinc, Manganese, Molybdenum, Copper, Nikel.

AGRO:00000179.label: molybdenum area density
AGRO:00000179.definition: An area density quality which inheres in molybdenum by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of molybdenum applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000168.label: nitrate area density
AGRO:00000168.definition: An area density quality which inheres in nitrate by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of nitrate applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000158.label: nitrogen area density
AGRO:00000158.definition: An area density quality which inheres in nitrogen by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of nitrogen applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000160.label: phosphorus area density
AGRO:00000160.definition: An area density quality which inheres in phosphorus by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of phosphorus applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000205.label: plant reproductive material area density
AGRO:00000205.definition: An area density quality which inheres in plant reproductive material by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of plant reproductive material planted in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000201.label: potassium area density
AGRO:00000201.definition: An area density quality which inheres in potassium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of potassium applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000447.label: rhizobium area density
AGRO:00000447.definition: An area density quality which inheres in rhizobium by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of rhizobium inoculated into the soil.

AGRO:00000164.label: sulfur area density
AGRO:00000164.definition: An area density quality which inheres in sulfur by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of sulfur applied in a given surface area.

AGRO:00000176.label: zinc area density
AGRO:00000176.definition: An area density quality which inheres in zinc by virtue of some influence exerted by the mass of zinc applied in a given surface area.

PATO:0001456.label: anaerobic
PATO:0001456.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's independence on oxygen.

AGRO:00000448.label: nitrogen recovery efficiency
AGRO:00000448.definition: Amount of nutrient in the crop as a ratio of the amount applied or available.

AGRO:00000450.label: nitrogen use efficiency
AGRO:00000450.definition: Ratio between the amount of nitrogen fertilizer removed from the field by the crop and the amount of nitrogen fertilizer applied. It provides information about the relative utilization of additional nitrogen applied to a agricultural production system.

AGRO:00000452.label: organic fertilizer carbon to nitrogen ratio
AGRO:00000452.definition: Carbon-to-nitrogen ratio is a ratio of the mass of carbon to the mass of nitrogen in an organic fertilizer.

AGRO:00000348.label: percent of experiment area damaged
AGRO:00000348.definition: Percentage of the area of the experiment damaged due to a complication during the experiment.

PATO:0001688.label: increased elevation
PATO:0001688.definition: An elevation which is relatively high.

PATO:0001689.label: decreased elevation
PATO:0001689.definition: An elevation which is relatively low.

PATO:0001504.label: complex
PATO:0001504.definition: A complexity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being intricate and compounded.

PATO:0001545.label: inflexible
PATO:0001545.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's inability of being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

PATO:0001543.label: flexibility
PATO:0001543.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being turned, bowed, or twisted without breaking.

PATO:0000048.label: hardness
PATO:0000048.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's resistance to pressure, being broken, or pierced

PATO:0015009.label: humidity
PATO:0015009.definition: A quality inhering in air by virtue of the partial pressure exerted by the bearer's water vapour content.

PATO:0000992.label: viscosity
PATO:0000992.definition: A physical quality of a liquid inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to internal resistance to flow.

PATO:0001757.label: electrical conductivity
PATO:0001757.definition: A conductivity quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to convey electricity.

PATO:0002254.label: flattened
PATO:0002254.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's surface becoming more extended in a plane.

AGRO:00010007.label: residue incorporation depth
AGRO:00010007.definition: The depth of a crop residue

AGRO:00010002.label: tillage depth
AGRO:00010002.definition: The depth of a tillage process

PATO:0001657.label: increased osmolarity
PATO:0001657.definition: A osmolarity which is relatively high.

AGRO:00000367.label: experimental site altitude
AGRO:00000367.definition: Elevation above the sea level of the experimental site.

AGRO:00000368.label: weather station altitude
AGRO:00000368.definition: Elevation above sea level of the weather station.

PATO:0001595.label: depth
PATO:0001595.definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

PATO:0001334.label: diameter
PATO:0001334.definition: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes through the center of a circle and whose endpoints are on the circular boundary.

PATO:0000119.label: height
PATO:0000119.definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's vertical dimension of extension.

PATO:0000122.label: length
PATO:0000122.definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

PATO:0000915.label: thickness
PATO:0000915.definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the dimension through an object as opposed to its length or width.

PATO:0000921.label: width
PATO:0000921.definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance from one side of an object to another side which is opposite.

PATO:0001323.label: area
PATO:0001323.definition: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

PATO:0000918.label: volume
PATO:0000918.definition: A 3-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's amount of 3-dimensional space it occupies.

PATO:0001734.label: semi-deciduous(plant)
PATO:0001734.definition: A quality inhering in a plant by virtue of the bearer's disposition to being between evergeen and deciduous.

PATO:0001291.label: electromagnetic (EM) radiation quality
PATO:0001291.definition: A physical quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with electromagnetic radiation.

PATO:0001824.label: dry
PATO:0001824.definition: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's not being covered by a liquid.

PATO:0001823.label: wet
PATO:0001823.definition: A wetness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being covered by a liquid.

PATO:0001428.label: medium acidity
PATO:0001428.definition: A concentration quality inhering in a medium by virtue of the bearer's tendency to hydronate a specific reference base.

PATO:0001574.label: flow rate
PATO:0001574.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's motion characteristic.

PATO:0000008.label: speed
PATO:0000008.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's scalar absolute value of the rate of change of the bearer's position.

PATO:0000186.label: behavioral quality
PATO:0000186.definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's behavior aggregate of the responses or reactions or movements in a given situation.

PATO:0000261.label: maturity
PATO:0000261.definition: A quality of a single physical entity which is held by a bearer when the latter exhibits a state of growth, differentiation, or development.

PATO:0000085.label: sensitivity toward
PATO:0000085.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to detect or perceive external stimulation.

PATO:0001729.label: shedability
PATO:0001729.definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to lose an entitity by natural process.

PATO:0001309.label: duration
PATO:0001309.definition: A process quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude of the temporal extent between the starting and ending point.

PATO:0000161.label: rate
PATO:0000161.definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence per unit time.

PATO:0002323.label: temporal distribution quality
PATO:0002323.definition: A temporal distribution pattern of process occurrences within a regulation/reference process.

PATO:0002068.label: stratified
PATO:0002068.definition: A spatial pattern inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's exhibiting a layered configuration.

PATO:0000033.label: concentration of
PATO:0000033.definition: A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

PATO:0002204.label: ambidextrous handedness
PATO:0002204.definition: Handedness where the organism exhibits no overall dominance in the use of right or left hand or foot in the performance of tasks that require one hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

PATO:0002202.label: left handedness
PATO:0002202.definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the left hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

PATO:0002203.label: right handedness
PATO:0002203.definition: Handedness where the organism preferentially uses the right hand or foot for tasks requiring the use of a single hand or foot or a dominant hand or foot.

PATO:0000407.label: flat
PATO:0000407.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having a horizontal surface without a slope, tilt, or curvature.

PATO:0000057.label: occurrence
PATO:0000057.definition: A quality of a single process inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's occurrence.

PATO:0000044.label: frequency
PATO:0000044.definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of the number of the bearer's repetitive actions in a particular time.

PCO:0000028.label: community
PCO:0000028.definition: A collection of organisms of the same species whose members are all either genealogically related to each other or have mated with each other.

PCO:0000029.label: multi-species collection of organisms
PCO:0000029.definition: A collection of organisms that consists of two or more organisms from at least two species.

PCO:0000018.label: single-species collection of organisms
PCO:0000018.definition: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.

PCO:0000001.label: population of organisms
PCO:0000001.definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

PCO:0000002.label: ecological community
PCO:0000002.definition: A community of at least two different species, living in a particular area. Must have at least two populations of different species as members.

CARO:0001010.label: organism or virus or viroid
CARO:0001010.definition: Material anatomical entity that is a member of an individual species or is a viral or viroid particle.

PO:0009009.label: plant embryo
PO:0009009.definition: A whole plant (PO:0000003) that participates in the plant embryo stage (PO:0007631).

PO:0025222.label: reproductive shoot apex
PO:0025222.definition: A shoot apex that has as part a reproductive shoot apical meristem.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 生殖シュート頂、茎頂 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0004709.label: axillary bud
PO:0004709.definition: A bud (PO:0000055) that develops from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232).

PO:0006343.label: axillary shoot system
PO:0006343.definition: A shoot-borne shoot system (PO:0004545) that develops from an axillary bud (PO:0004709).

PO:0009055.label: bract
PO:0009055.definition: A phyllome that subtends a reproductive structure.

PO:0025034.label: leaf
PO:0025034.definition: A phyllome (PO:0006001) that is not associated with a reproductive structure.

PO:0020148.label: shoot apical meristem
PO:0020148.definition: A shoot system meristem (PO:0006079) formed at the apex of the shoot axis (PO:0025029), including those originating from an axillary bud meristem (PO:0000232).

PO:0005001.label: basal axillary shoot system
PO:0005001.definition: An axillary shoot system (PO:0006343) that is part of a stem base (PO:0008039).

PO:0025337.label: life of whole plant stage
PO:0025337.definition: A maximal whole plant development stage.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: vida de la planta entera (Spanish, exact)

PO:0028002.label: sporophyte development stage
PO:0028002.definition: A whole plant development stage (PO:0007033) that has as primary participant a whole plant (PO:0000003) during the interval between fertilization (or apogamy) and death.

PO:0000229.label: flower meristem
PO:0000229.definition: A portion of reproductive shoot apical meristem tissue (PO:0008028) that gives rise to the floral organs (PO:0025395).

PO:0030108.label: berry fruit
PO:0030108.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which at maturity comprises a fleshy endocarp (PO:0009086), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085).

PO:0030104.label: caryopsis fruit
PO:0030104.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are fused to a seed coat (PO:0009088).

PO:0030100.label: legume fruit
PO:0030100.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that dehisce along two fruit valves (PO:0000033).

PO:0025606.label: native plant cell
PO:0025606.definition: A plant cell (PO:0009002) that is either part of a multicellular whole plant (PO:0000003) 'in vivo' or a unicellular organism 'in natura' (i.e. part of a natural environment).

PO:0025523.label: tuberous root
PO:0025523.definition: A root (PO:0009005) that is radially enlarged relative to other lateral roots (PO:0020121) or shoot-borne roots (PO:0000042) on the same plant, but not as enlarged as a tuberous root tuber (PO:0025476).

PO:0025476.label: tuberous root tuber
PO:0025476.definition: A root (PO:0009005) that develops from a tuberous root (PO:0025523) and is further radially enlarged for storage.

PO:0025082.label: reproductive shoot system
PO:0025082.definition: A shoot system (PO:0009006) in the sporophytic phase that has as part at least one sporangium (PO:0025094).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 生殖シュート 系、苗条系 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0004545.label: shoot-borne shoot system
PO:0004545.definition: A shoot system that is initiated from a shoot.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: シュート由来苗条系 (Japanese, exact)
sistema de epiblasto (epiblastema) que nace en el epiblasto (epiblastema) (Spanish, exact)

PO:0009085.label: exocarp
PO:0009085.definition: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the outer layer of a pericarp (PO:0009084).

PO:0009087.label: mesocarp
PO:0009087.definition: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is the middle layer of a pericarp (PO:0009084).

PO:0025233.label: portion of embryo plant tissue
PO:0025233.definition: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 植物胚性組織 の一部   (Japanese, exact)
植物胚性組織 の一部   (Japanese, exact)

PO:0009013.label: portion of meristem tissue
PO:0009013.definition: A portion of plant tissue (PO:0009007) in which plant cells (PO:0009002) have retained their embryonic characteristics, or have reverted to them secondarily, and that divide to produce new cells that can undergo differentiation to form mature tissues, i.e. they have a capacity for morphogenesis and growth.

PO:0025395.label: floral organ
PO:0025395.definition: A plant organ (PO:0009008) that is part of a flower (PO:0009046).

PO:0006001.label: phyllome
PO:0006001.definition: A lateral plant organ (PO:0009008) produced by a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: フィロム、葉(的）器官 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0020003.label: plant ovule
PO:0020003.definition: A plant organ (PO:0009008) that has as parts a nucellus (PO:0020020) in which a female gametophyte (PO:0025279) is located, one or two integuments (PO:0020021), and a funicle (PO:0020006).

PO:0025498.label: cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure
PO:0025498.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is a proper part of a multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) and includes portions of plant tissues (PO:0009007) of at least two different types.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: parte cardinal de estructura vegetal con m&#250ltiples tejidos (Spanish, exact)
複数の組織からなる植物構造の基本（主要）部分 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0025497.label: collective plant structure
PO:0025497.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003) and includes two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) or adjacent cardinal organ parts (PO:0025001), along with any associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007).

PO:0025099.label: embryo plant structure
PO:0025099.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that is part of an plant embryo (PO:0009009).

PO:0025496.label: multi-tissue plant structure
PO:0025496.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that has as parts two or more portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single structural unit demarcated by primarily bona-fide boundaries from other structural units of different types.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 複数の組織からなる植物構造 (Japanese, exact)
estructura vegetal con m&#250ltiples tejidos (Spanish, exact)

PO:0009002.label: plant cell
PO:0009002.definition: A cell which is a plant structure (PO:0009011).

PO:0009007.label: portion of plant tissue
PO:0009007.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that consists predominantly of similarly specialized plant cells (PO:0009002) of one or more types.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: porci&#243n de un tejido vegetal (Spanish, exact)

PO:0020144.label: apical meristem
PO:0020144.definition: A maximal portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) located at a shoot apex (PO:0000037) or root tip (PO:0000025).

PO:0000225.label: peripheral zone
PO:0000225.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) which is the organogenic region of the meristem, characterized by higher rates of cell division.

PO:0025430.label: phyllome anlagen
PO:0025430.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a peripheral zone (PO:0000225) of a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and will give rise to a phyllome primordium (PO:0025128).

PO:0025127.label: primordium
PO:0025127.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that has as parts protoderm (PO:0006210) and sub-epidermal meristematic tissue and is committed to the development of a particular plant structure (PO:0009011).

PO:0006210.label: protoderm
PO:0006210.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is the outer layer of an apical meristem (PO:0020144), or the outer layer of a plant embryo proper (PO:0000001), and gives rise to a portion of epidermis (PO:0005679).

PO:0025433.label: root anlagen
PO:0025433.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is committed to the development of a root primordium (PO:0005029).

PO:0006079.label: shoot system meristem
PO:0006079.definition: A portion of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: シュート分裂組織 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0008028.label: reproductive shoot apical meristem
PO:0008028.definition: A shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) that gives rise to the apical growth of reproductive tissues and organs.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 生殖シュート頂端 分裂組織 (Japanese, exact)
meristema apical reproductivo del epiblasto (epiblastema) (Spanish, exact)

PO:0009005.label: root
PO:0009005.definition: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that lacks shoot axis nodes (PO:0005004) and usually grows indeterminately.

PO:0025029.label: shoot axis
PO:0025029.definition: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that is part of a shoot system (PO:0009006).

PO:0025522.label: tuber
PO:0025522.definition: A plant axis (PO:0025004) that is radially enlarged.

PO:0025023.label: collective phyllome structure
PO:0025023.definition: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that consists of two or more phyllomes (PO:0006001) originating from the same node or from one or more adjacent nodes with compressed shoot internodes (PO:0005005).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 葉的器官が集まった構造 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0025025.label: root system
PO:0025025.definition: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces root meristems (PO:0006085), the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them and the parts thereof.

PO:0009006.label: shoot system
