PO:0009006.definition: A collective plant organ structure (PO:0025007) that produces shoot-borne portions of meristem tissue (PO:0009013) and the plant structures (PO:0009011) that arise from them.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: シュート系、苗条系 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0009062.label: gynoecium
PO:0009062.definition: A collective phyllome structure (PO:0025023) composed all of the carpels (PO:0009030) in a flower (PO:0009046).
oboInOwl:hasNarrowSynonym: gynoecium of lower floret of sessile spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium of upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (narrow)
gynoecium of upper floret of sessile spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium of lower floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (narrow)
gynoecium of lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium of upper floret of pedicellate spikelet of ear (narrow)
gynoecium of lower floret of pedicellate spikelet of tassel (narrow)
gynoecium of upper floret of sessile spikelet of tassel (narrow)

PO:0000037.label: shoot axis apex
PO:0000037.definition: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is the most distal part of a shoot system (PO:0009006) and has as parts a shoot apical meristem (PO:0020148) and the youngest primordia (PO:0025127).

PO:0009047.label: stem
PO:0009047.definition: A shoot axis (PO:0025029) that is the primary axis of a plant.

PO:0009046.label: flower
PO:0009046.definition: A determinate reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082) that has as part at least one carpel (PO:0009030) or at least one stamen (PO:0009029) and does not contain any other determinate shoot system (PO:0009006) as a part.

PO:0025028.label: embryo plant cell
PO:0025028.definition: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) that is part of a plant embryo (PO:0009009).

PO:0025477.label: floral organ primordium
PO:0025477.definition: A primordium (PO:0025127) that is committed to the development of a floral organ (PO:0025395) and is part of a reproductive shoot apex (PO:0025222).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: portion of floral structure primordium tissue (exact)

PO:0025128.label: phyllome primordium
PO:0025128.definition: A primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) and is part of a shoot apex (PO:0000037) and is committed to the development of a phyllome (PO:0006001).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: フィロム原基（可視的）  (Japanese, exact)

PO:0005029.label: root primordium
PO:0005029.definition: A primordium (PO:0025127) that develops from a root anlagen (PO:0025433) and is committed to the development of a root (PO:0009005).

PO:0025487.label: bract primordium
PO:0025487.definition: A phyllome primordium (PO:0025487) that is committed to the development of a flower bract (PO:0009055).

AGRO:00000032.label: plant reproductive material
AGRO:00000032.definition: A plant anatomical entity that is defined to mean plants or parts of plant capable of and intended for producing or reproducing entire plants.

PO:0025527.label: shoot system development stage
PO:0025527.definition: A collective plant organ structure development stage (PO:0025338) that begins with the onset of the plant organ development stage (PO:0025339) and ends with either gametophyte senescent stage (PO:0025343) or sporophyte senescent stage (PO:0007017) or death.

PO:0025482.label: bract anlagen
PO:0025482.definition: A phyllome anlagen (PO:0025430) that will give rise to a bract primordium (PO:0025487) and is part of a peripheral zone (PO:000225) of a reproductive shoot apical meristem (PO:0008028).

PO:0000019.label: gynoecium primordium
PO:0000019.definition: A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of a gynoecium (PO:0009062).

PO:0000018.label: ovule primordium
PO:0000018.definition: A floral structure primordium (PO:0025477) that is committed to the development of an ovule (PO:0020003).

PO:0025489.label: inflorescence bract primordium
PO:0025489.definition: A bract primordium (PO:0025128) is committed to the development of an inflorescence bract (PO:0009054).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: primordio de la br&#225ctea de la inflorescencia (Spanish, exact)

PO:0009001.label: fruit
PO:0009001.definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062), or a single carpel (PO:0009030), and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

PO:0009008.label: plant organ
PO:0009008.definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that is a functional unit, is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and includes portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types that derive from a common developmental path.

PO:0025007.label: collective plant organ structure
PO:0025007.definition: A collective plant structure (PO:0025497) that is a proper part of a whole plant (PO:0000003), and is composed of two or more adjacent plant organs (PO:0009008) and the associated portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 集合植物器官構造 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0025001.label: cardinal organ part
PO:0025001.definition: A cardinal part of multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025498) that is a proper part of a plant organ (PO:0009008) and includes portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: 基本的な（主要な）器官部 (Japanese, exact)

PO:0025528.label: bud development stage
PO:0025528.definition: A shoot system development stage (PO:0025527) that has as primary participant a bud (PO:0009006).

PO:0025530.label: reproductive shoot system development stage
PO:0025530.definition: A shoot system development stage (PO:0025527) that has as primary participant a reproductive shoot system (PO:0025082).

PO:0001083.label: inflorescence development stage
PO:0001083.definition: A reproductive shoot system development stage (PO:0025530) that has as primary participant a inflorescence (PO:0009049).

PO:0004010.label: meristematic cell
PO:0004010.definition: A native plant cell (PO:0025606) synthesizing protoplasm and producing new cells by division and with only a primary cell wall.

PO:0030109.label: hesperidium fruit
PO:0030109.definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from a superior gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a thickened exocarp (PO:0009085), thickened mesocarp (PO:0009087), and endocarp (PO:0009086), and has as parts juice sacs (PO:0006013) on a carpel adaxial epidermis (PO:0025618).

ENVO:01000254.label: environmental system
ENVO:01000254.definition: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.

UO:0000015.label: centimeter
UO:0000015.definition: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

UO:0000008.label: meter
UO:0000008.definition: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

UO:0000016.label: millimeter
UO:0000016.definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

UO:0000021.label: gram
UO:0000021.definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a kilogram or 10^[-3] kg.

UO:0000009.label: kilogram
UO:0000009.definition: A mass unit which is equal to the mass of the International Prototype Kilogram kept by the BIPM at Svres, France.

UO:0000022.label: milligram
UO:0000022.definition: A mass unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gram or 10^[-3] g.

UO:0000033.label: day
UO:0000033.definition: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

UO:0000032.label: hour
UO:0000032.definition: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

UO:0000031.label: minute
UO:0000031.definition: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

UO:0000035.label: month
UO:0000035.definition: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

UO:0000010.label: second
UO:0000010.definition: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

UO:0000034.label: week
UO:0000034.definition: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

UO:0000036.label: year
UO:0000036.definition: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which in science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

UO:0000027.label: degree Celsius
UO:0000027.definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

UO:0000195.label: degree Fahrenheit
UO:0000195.definition: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

UO:0000163.label: mass percentage
UO:0000163.definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

UO:0000196.label: pH
UO:0000196.definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

UO:0000092.label: turns per second
UO:0000092.definition: A rotational frequency unit which is equal to the number complete turn in a period of time that equals to 1 second.

UO:0000197.label: liter per kilogram
UO:0000197.definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one liter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

UO:0000099.label: liter
UO:0000099.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

UO:0000098.label: milliliter
UO:0000098.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

UO:0000059.label: specific volume unit
UO:0000059.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a given mass of substance (the reciprocal of density).

UO:0000058.label: rotational frequency unit
UO:0000058.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the number of rotations in a given time.

UO:0000271.label: microliters per minute
UO:0000271.definition: A volumetric flow rate unit which is equal to one microliter volume through a given surface in one minute.
